Commentary: EDGY WAY TO START! Anderson starts with a good length ball on middle and leg. Masood looks to flick it off his pads but it takes the leading edge and goes towards gully.

DEAD BALL! Anderson has not got his line right to the left-hander! On a length on the pads, Masood leaves it. It hits his thigh pad and goes to the fence. The umpire signals it a dead ball as no shot was attempted.
Good length delivery outside off, Masood leaves the ball alone.
BEATEN! Beautiful from James Anderson. Just where he would want to be to Masood. Good length ball around off, moving away. Masood looks to defend it off the front foot but fails to get any bat on it.
Anderson dishes a length ball outside off, Masood watches the ball carefully and leaves the ball alone.
Good probing start from Anderson! He finishes the over by bowling a length ball on middle, Masood blocks it to the cover region. A maiden over to start.
Pakistan are underway! Broad starts with a full delivery on middle, with little swing on it. Abid defends it to cover and calls Masood for a single.
Broad comes around the wicket and bowls a fuller one around off, Shan goes on the front foot and defends it to point.
On a length on middle, Masood flicks it to mid-wicket.
Good length ball outside off, angling in sharply, Masood does not bother playing at that one.
Masood is off the mark! Full delivery on off, Masood defends it to the off side and takes a single.
On a length on middle, Ali tucks it to square leg.
BEATEN! Once again Anderson goes past the bat of Masood! Just brilliant from Anderson! Good length ball outside off, moving away. Masood looks to defend but fails to get any bat on it.
FOUR LEG BYES! Good length delivery on the pads, Masood attempts to flick but it hits the thigh pad and goes past the diving keeper and into the fine leg fence.
BEATEN! Anderson has started really well here! He is troubling Masood very early on in the innings. Full delivery outside off, Shan looks to put bat on ball but misses it completely.
On a length on middle, Masood blocks it to mid on.
Back of a length ball on middle, Masood solidly plays it towards mid on.
On a length outside off, Masood shoulders arms to it.
Wayward delivery from Broad! You don't see this everyday! Good length ball down the leg side, Abid lets it go. Buttler dives to his left and makes a half-stop. A bye taken.
Good length ball on middle, Shan blocks it back to the bowler.
Fullish ball on the middle stump line, Shan defends it out onto the pitch.
Good length ball outside off, Masood lets it go to the keeper.
Good length ball outside off, Shan leaves it alone.
BEATEN! Lovely finish to the over from Broad! Good length ball outside off, Masood attempts to defend it off the back foot but the ball whizzes past the outside edge and into the mitts of the keeper.
BEATEN! Massive movement there! On a length around off, moving away sharply. Abid looks to block but fails to make any connection with it.
Full ball on the pads, Ali flicks it to fine leg for a single.
Good length ball outside off, Masood has no problems in leaving it alone.
Good length ball on off, Masood is solid in defense.
EDGY RUN! Nicely bowled from Anderson! Good length ball on off, moving in, Masood looks to defend but it takes the inside edge, hits the pads and goes towards square leg. A single taken.
BEATEN! Wow, what a delivery from Anderson! Good length ball outside off, moving away. Abid looks to defend but misses it altogether.
Good length ball on the pads, Masood looks to flick but gets hit on the thigh pad. No run.
On a length on middle, Masood tucks it to square leg. He wants the single but is sent back.
Full ball on off, Masood prods forward and blocks it to cover.
EDGY! Broad dishes a full delivery on off, Masood looks to defend but it goes off the outside edge towards gully.

FOUR! Masood was not sure what to do there! Back of a length ball outside off, Masood first attempts to play at it but then looks to withdraw it. It hits the bat and goes through the gully region for a boundary.
Full on middle, Masood defends it back to the bowler.
BEATEN! Another one which goes past the bat! Good length ball outside off, Ali attempts to put bat on ball but fails.
PLAY AND A MISS! Anderson might feel unlucky not to have got an edge yet! Good length ball outside off, swinging away. Abid gets beaten as he attempts to defend this one.
On a length on the pads, Abid flicks it to fine leg for a single.
Full delivery outside off, Masood lets it through to the keeper.

EDGY FOUR! Frustration for Anderson! He has beaten Masood many times and when it takes the edge, the ball races to the fence. Good length ball on off, Masood looks to block but it takes the outside edge and goes past the slip cordon and into the third man fence.
Good length ball down the leg side, Masood looks to flick but fails to make any contact with it.
Length and it starts outside off, does come in a bit. Ali plays inside the line, the ball whizzes past the outside edge. It was a long way away though.
Outside off, Ali shoulders arms to this one.
Slightly fuller and on middle, Ali plays a solid drive to mid on.
Another one on the middle pole, Ali works it to mid-wicket. Broad is looking to hit the front pad of Ali. He is hoping Abid falls across as he plants his front foot down.
Now goes outside off, Ali shoulders arms to this one.

Close shave! Abid Ali goes for an expansive drive to this delivery outside off. He went a little too hard at it and hence, got an inside edge. It was going towards the stumps but then it hits the back leg and deflects away. Lucky.
Outside off, left alone.
A single as this is worked around the corner.
FOUR! A little too straight and Ali puts it away in style! Full and on the pads, Abid works it through square leg to bring up his first boundary.

FOUR! Second boundary for Ali! This one is lucky. It was uppish but just out of the reach. Shorter and outside off, Ali looks to play the back foot punch but does so away from the body. It flies off the outside edge but just wide of the diving gully fielder and down to the third man fence. Ali is riding his luck here.
BEATEN! Length and just outside off, Abid looks to defend but fails to get any bat on it.
Good length and on off, Ali defends it onto the ground. A good over for Pakistan, 9 from it.
On the pads, it is worked through square leg for one.
Length and on off, comes back a little. Ali looks to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
BEAUTY! Gets the last one to come back and this one holds its line. It lands on off, Ali has to play at it. He goes back to defend but the movement sees the ball beat the outside edge.
Solid defense! On off, defended nicely.
Gets off strike! Ali stands tall and pushes it towards the off side for one.
A good nut to end! Comes from around the wicket to the left-hander. Lands it outside off and gets it to jag back in. Masood looks to block but misses to get hit high on the pads.
Starts off with a decent outswinger. The line though is just outside off. Ali shoulders arms to this one.
Bowls this one on the stumps, Ali defends it nicely.
Well bowled! This is fuller and around off, it shapes away a touch. Ali looks to play it with a straight bat but it goes off the outer half through covers for one.
BEATEN! Gets the ball to move off the pitch! It is a length delivery around off, Masood lunges to keep it out but it pitches and shapes away. Beats the outside edge.

Appeal but a soft one! Woakes has started well here. He is getting the ball to move both ways. He lands this on a length, similar line to the last ball and gets it to come back in. Masood looks to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
A dot to end a testing over! Back of a length and around off, Masood keeps it out.

Broad almost got Ali there! He continues angling it into the pads of Ali. Abid does plant his front foot a little too across this time but manages to get his bat down right at the end. He gets an inside edge onto the pads. No inside edge, he would have been a goner.
Outside off, left alone.
Another one outside off, not played at.
A short one, Ali fends it away uncomfortably towards fine leg for one.
Outside off, left alone.
Back of a length delivery on off, Masood taps it towards the off side for a quick single.
Full ball on middle, Masood pushes it to mid on.
Good length ball on middle, Masood blocks it back to the bowler.
Good length ball around off, angling in. Masood lets it go to the keeper.
Outside off, left alone.
On a length on middle, Shan comfortably tucks it to mid-wicket.
MAIDEN! Fullish ball outside off, Masood lets it go to the keeper.
Archer starts with an incoming full delivery on middle, Ali works it to the fine leg region for a single.
Archer dishes a back of a length ball on off, Masood blocks it to cover and collects a single.
Good length ball outside off, Abid lets the ball through to the keeper.
Another one which is outside off, Ali shoulders arms to this one.
There comes the short one! Archer bends his back and bowls a short one around middle, Ali plays it well as he ducks under it.
Short one outside off, Ali sways away from it.
Good running! Good length ball on middle, Masood tucks it wide of mid on and takes a single.
Back of a length ball on middle, Ali flicks it to square leg for a single.
On a length on middle, Shan plays it back to the bowler.
Full delivery outside off, Masood pushes it to the point region.
Good length ball outside off, Masood shoulders arms to it.
Good length ball on middle, Masood defends it back to the bowler.

OUT! TIMBER! That's a ripper from Archer! A full delivery does the trick for England. A good little start comes to an end for Pakistan. Archer bowled a couple of bouncers at the end of his previous over but this time, he dishes a full delivery on off, nipping in, Ali looks to push but is trapped in his crease as the ball hits the pads and goes onto hit the off stump. Just terrific from Archer. Abid was probably expecting a bouncer but got surprised by the length of the delivery and was beaten by the pace.
BOUNCER! It is bowled outside off, Azhar sways away from it.
Good length ball on off, Ali prods forward and defends it to cover.
On a length outside off, Azhar shoulders arms to it.
Good length ball on off, Azhar defends it to the off side.
Short ball around middle, Ali ducks under it.
Woakes bowls a full delivery on middle, Masood drives it through mid off and picks up a couple.
Back of a length ball on off, Masood camps back and blocks it to cover.
Fullish ball outside off, Masood lets the ball through to the keeper.
Good length ball on middle, Masood blocks it back to the bowler.
Late movement! Good length ball outside off, moving in late. Masood leaves it alone. Buttler dives and makes a good stop.
On a length on the pads, Shan flicks it to mid-wicket for a single.
BEATEN! Excellent bowling from Archer! Good length ball outside off, moving away, Masood attempts to defend but fails to get any bat on it.
EDGY FOUR! Masood will take it however they come! Good length ball around off, Masood looks to defend but it goes off the outside edge through the gully region for a boundary.
Full delivery on middle, Shan plays it back to the bowler.
On a length on middle, Masood works it to mid-wicket.
Good length ball outside off, Masood does not bother to play at that one.
Good length ball on middle and leg, Masood blocks it to mid on.

OUT! LBW! All reds it is and Ali has to go. Ali thought that there was some bat on it but that wasn't the case. This is terrific bowling from Chris Woakes. He was exceptional in the last Test against West Indies and he has started well here too. Good length ball around off, nipping in sharply. Ali looks to flick but gets rapped on the pads. England appeal and the umpire raises his finger. Azhar takes the review immediately. The Ultra Edge shows no bat while the Ball Tracker shows that it is pitching in line and it is going onto hit the stumps. Poor review from the Pakistan skipper. He probably must have heard the noise of the bat hitting the pad.
BEATEN! Wow, what a way to welcome Babar Azam. Absolutely brilliant. Good length ball around off, moving away. Azam looks to defend but misses it altogether.
Good length ball on the pads, Azam looks to flick but gets hit on the pads. The ball rolls to the leg side and a leg bye is taken.
Outside off, left alone.
On a length on middle, Masood defends it out.
Good length ball on middle, defended out onto the pitch.
On a good length on off, Azam defends it off the back foot.
Good length delivery on off, Azam keeps it out.
Outside off, Azam offers no shot to this one.
Archer bowls a bouncer outside off, Azam does well to duck under it.
Good length delivery on off, Azam blocks it off the back foot.
On a good length on off, Babar offers a solid defense on this one.
Good length delivery outside off, Masood shoulders arms to this one.
On a good length and outside off, Masood leaves it alone.

EDGY FOUR! Lucky for Masood! Good length ball outside off, Masood looks to defend but it takes the outside edge and goes towards Sibley at second slip. Sibley dives and manages to get a slight hand on it but hits his hand and goes to the third man fence.
On a length on middle, Masood defends it back to the bowler.
Good length ball on the pads, Masood looks to flick but misses and gets hit on the pads. There is an appeal made for LBW but noting from the umpire.
On middle, Masood defends it back to the bowler.
Good length ball on middle, Babar blocks it back to the bowler.
Full ball on off, Azam is solid in defense.
Shortish down the leg side, Babar looks to work it to the leg side but misses.
Good length ball on middle, Azam blocks it to the bowler.
Azam leaves this good length ball outside off alone.
Good length ball on off, Azam blocks it to the point region.
Good length ball on the pads, Masood looks to flick but gets hit on the pads.

An appeal for LBW turned down! Probably pitched outside leg. Slightly fuller on the leg stump line, Masood looks to drive but he misses and hits the pad. Woakes and England appeal but the umpire is not interested. They think of the review but decide against it and rightly so as the Ball Tracker shows that it is pitching outside leg.
Good length ball on middle, Masood defends it out onto the pitch.
Fullish on middle, Masood pushes it to mid on.
Back of a length on middle, Masood works it to mid-wicket for a single.
Babar is off the mark finally! Full ball on off, Azam pushes it to cover and takes a single.
Good length ball on middle, Azam works it to short leg.
Full ball on off, Azam pushes it to the cover fielder.
Lovely drive! Good length ball outside off, Babar drives it crisply but finds the cover fielder.
BEATEN! Beautiful piece of bowling from Archer! Good length ball outside off, Azam looks to defend but fails to get any bat on it.
Bouncer bowled around middle, Azam ducks under it.
Length ball on middle, Babar flicks it to deep square leg and picks up a single.
Good length ball outside off, Azam looks to defend at first but then decides to leave it alone.

EDGY! Full ball on middle, Azam looks to flick but it takes the leading edge and goes to point. The fielder throws it to the keeper's end but it hits the bat of Azam and lobs off to Archer at square leg.
On a length on middle, Azam defends it back to the bowler.
BEATEN! Lovely from Woakes! He bowls a good length ball around off, moving away. Azam looks to defend but fails to get any bat on it.
Length ball outside off, Babar lets the ball through to the keeper.
Full toss on the pads, Babar flicks it through mid-wicket for a couple to end the session. LUNCH ON DAY 1.
Lovely start to the session for Broad! Beautiful delivery! Good length ball outside off, Masood looks to defend but the ball whizzes past the outside edge and into the mitts of the keeper.
Full ball on middle, Masood flicks it to mid-wicket.
On a length on middle, Shan rocks on his back foot and defends it back to the bowler.
Broad bowls a good length ball outside off, Shan shoulders arms to it.
Fullish ball on off, Masood prods forward and pushes it to cover.
A maiden to start the second session! Good length ball on off, Masood blocks it to gully off the back foot.
FOUR! Anderson starts with a poor delivery! Full delivery on the pads, Azam just helps it on its way to the fine leg region for a boundary.
Good length ball on off, Azam defends it to cover.
Full ball on middle, Babar looks to defend but it takes the leading edge and goes towards the off side for a single.
On a length on middle, Masood flicks it to square leg.
Good length ball outside off, Masood watches it carefully and lets it go to the keeper.
Outside off, not played at.
On a length on leg, Azam flicks it towards fine leg for a single.
Good length delivery outside off, Masood offers no shot to this one.
FOUR! Crunched from Masood! He is looking good! Back of a length ball outside off, Masood punches it through the point region for a boundary.
On a length on middle, Shan flicks it to mid-wicket.
Fullish ball outside off, Masood shoulders arms to it.
Good length ball on off, Shan solidly blocks it to cover.
Anderson dishes a length ball on middle, Azam tucks it to mid-wicket.

FOUR! Anderson has started well after Lunch! Azam is a very good player off his pads and he will not miss out on these freebies! Full delivery on the pads, Azam clips it through mid-wicket for a boundary.
Good length ball on middle, Azam nudges it to mid-wicket for a couple.
Good length ball outside off, Azam leaves the ball alone.
Good length ball outside off, Azam has no problems in leaving it alone.
On a length on off, Babar defends it to mid off.
Good length ball on middle, Masood blocks it back to the bowler.
Back of a length on off, Shan blocks it to cover.
On a length on off, Masood guides it to gully and wants a single. Azam though sends him back.
Good length ball outside off, Masood lets the ball go to the keeper.
On middle, Masood blocks it back to the bowler.

Half an appeal! A beautiful nut to end the over! Good length ball around off, Masood looks to defend without moving his feet. He gets beaten. There's an appeal made for caught behind but nothing from the umpire.
Good length ball outside off, Azam leaves it alone.
Outside off, Azam shoulders arms to it.
Good length ball on middle, Babar defends it back to the bowler.
NO BALL! Another length ball on middle, Azam blocks it out onto the pitch. The third umpire gives it as a No Ball.
FOUR! Perfect balance and perfect timing! Back of a length ball outside off, Azam drives it nonchalantly through the covers for a boundary.
On a length on off, Azam defends it to the off side.
Azam solidly defends this length ball on off to cover.
On a good length on off, Masood defends it to covers.
Good length delivery on off, Masood blocks it off the back foot.
On a good length and outside off, Masood shoulders arms to this one.
Length delivery on middle, Masood flicks it to mid-wicket.
FOUR! Beautifully flicked away from Masood! Good length ball on middle, Masood flicks it towards deep square leg. Bess runs after it and dives but fails to stop it. A boundary signalled.
Very full ball on off, Masood defends it to cover.
Bess starts with a flat delivery on middle, Masood pulls it to mid on.
Loopy ball on off, Masood defends it to cover.
Short delivery outside off, Shan punches it to cover for a single.
Floated on middle, Babar plays it back to the bowler.
Full on the pads, Azam works it to short leg.
Flatter on middle, Babar works it to deep mid-wicket for a single.
FOUR! That's a gift from Broad and it has been put away! Full toss on middle, Azam drives it through mid on for a boundary.
Better from Broad! Good length ball outside off, nipping in. Azam watches it and lets the ball through to the keeper.
Outside off, left alone.
Full ball on middle, Azam defends it to mid-wicket.
Good length ball on middle, played back to the bowler.
Fullish outside off, Azam lets it go to the keeper.
Tossed up ball on middle and leg, Masood defends it out.
Flatter one on off, Shan pushes it to point.
Quicker delivery on the pads, Masood looks to flick but gets hit on the pads. The ball rolls to the keeper.
Tossed up ball on middle, Shan defends it back to the bowler.
Flatter one on middle, Masood works it to mid-wicket.
Loopy on off, Masood defends it back to the bowler.
FOUR! Azam welcomes Archer with a delicious shot! Archer starts with a loosener on middle, Azam just pushes it down to long on for a boundary.
Good length ball on middle, Azam works it to mid-wicket for a single.
Fullish on middle, Masood tucks it to the leg side.
Length ball on off, Masood pushes it to mid off.
BOUNCER! It is bowled around middle, Masood ducks under it.
Good length ball outside off, Masood shoulders arms to it.

FOUR! Babar Azam is looking in terrific touch! What a way to bring up the 50-run stand! It has been a good one and needs to continue on to a big one. Tossed up outside off, Azam lunges forward and drives it through extra cover for a boundary.
On off, Babar blocks it to cover and takes a single.
Loopy ball down the leg side, Masood looks to flick but misses.
Full on middle, Masood drives it to mid on and takes a quick single.
Tosses this one outside off, Babar prods forward and leaves it alone.
FOUR! That's another gorgeous drive from Azam! 100-up for Pakistan! Full outside off, Babar drives it towards the deep cover region for a boundary.
FOUR! Looking for the yorker but it ends up as a full toss! It is bowled on middle, Masood flicks it to deep square leg for a boundary.
Good length ball on middle, Masood defends it back to the bowler.
On a length on off, Masood pushes it to gully.
Back of a length ball down the leg side, Masood looks to flick but misses.
Good length ball on off, Masood stands tall and defends it out.
Short on middle, Masood defends it back to the bowler.
Full and outside off, it is stroked through covers for one.
Quicker and on middle, Masood keeps it out nicely.

That is mighty close! Masood does not pick the length there. It is quicker and on middle, Masood goes back to a delivery which he should have played forward to. It hits both the inside edge and the pads, goes just past the leg pole towards fine leg for one. There is a soft appeal but nothing from the umpire. Hold on! Replays show that it is pad first. That looked dead if it was pad first.
Floats it up on middle, this is eased down to long on for one.
A full toss, it is worked behind square on the leg side for two.

DROPPED! Buttler has put down Masood! A difficult chance but you expect the keeper to take it. Bess gives it nice amount of flight and it lands on off, it turns away sharply. Masood lunges forward and looks to defend but the ball takes a faint outside edge. Buttler fails to move his glove to the left, it hits the webbing and falls onto the ground. Bess could have had Masood not once but twice in the over. Two let offs for the left-hander. Also, Pakistan won't mind seeing the turn on offer for the spinner. Remember, they have two in their side.
Good length ball outside off, Azam leaves it alone.
Full delivery on off, Azam drives it to mid off.
FOUR! That is an excellent shot from Babar Azam! He is batting on a diferent planet at the moment! Back of a length ball outside off, Azam plays it through the cover region for a boundary.
BOUNCER! It is bowled outside off, Azam leaves it alone.
Short one outside off, Azam leaves it alone.
Bouncer! The batsman ducks under the bouncer at the last moment.
Floats it up on off, defended.
Flatter and on off, it is pushed towards cover.
Fires it on the pads, Masood goes back and tries to flick but is a little late on the shot. It hits the pad and rolls on the leg side. A leg bye taken.
On middle, defended nicely.
FOUR! Lovely use of the feet! Azam gets to the pitch of it and hits it up and over mid-wicket. He plays it with the turn and it goes for a one bounce boundary.

Fifty for Azam! His 14th in Tests. What a player he has become in the last year or so. He's scoring runs just for fun. He did struggle at the start of his innings but then has looked fluent as ever. He gets there by pushing it through covers for one. He would want to keep going here.
Played that well in the end! Short ball around middle, Babar is late in picking that up but manages to pull it to deep square leg for a couple.
Archer starts with a nasty bouncer around middle, Azam ducks under it comfortably.
Back of a length ball on middle, Azam blocks it off the back foot to mid-wicket.
Shortish around the leg stump line, Babar fends it away towards fine leg and picks up a single.
Well played! Archer bends his back and bowls a short ball outside off, Masood camps on his back foot and then pushes it to point.
BOUNCER! It is bowled around middle, Masood ducks under it.
Floated on middle, Azam defends it back to the bowler.
Loopy ball on middle, flicked to square leg.
Flatter one on middle, Azam works it to short leg.
Tossed up ball on off, Azam defends it to cover and takes a single.
Quicker delivery outside off, Masood leaves it alone.
An appeal for LBW turned down! Floated on the pads, Masood looks to defend but misses to get hit on the pads. England appeal but nothing from the umpire. They think of a review but decide against it.
Root starts with a tossed up delivery on middle, Azam flicks it towards the leg side.
Loopy delivery on middle, Azam defends it off the back foot.
On middle, Azam flicks it towards square leg for a run.
Outside off, Masood offers no shot to this one.
Floated delivery on off, Masood plays it to covers.
On off, Masood blocks it off the front foot.
Floated on middle, Azam defends it to short leg.
Flatter one on middle, Azam flicks it to deep mid-wicket for a single.
Loopy ball on off, Masood pushes it to cover.
On middle, Shan tucks it to square leg.
Tossed up on off, Masood prods forward and drives it to mid off.
Loopy ball outside off, left alone.
Tossed up delivery on middle, Azam defends it off the back foot.
Flatter ball down the leg side, Azam lets it go. Buttler fails to collect it and the ball rolls to the leg side.
On off, defended to cover.
Flatter one on the pads, Azam tucks it to square leg.
Floated on middle, Azam defends it out onto the pitch.
Tossed up ball on middle, Azam nudges it towards mid-wicket for a single.
Flighted delivery on middle, Azam flicks it towards short leg.
Loopy delivery on off, Azam defends it off the front foot.
On middle, Azam comes down the track and flicks it through square leg for a single.

MISSED STUMPING! Masood gets another opportunity! He was dropped earlier in the game and now has been given another opportunity from Buttler. Poor keeping but it was probably the extra bounce that did Jos in. Floated ball outside off, Masood comes down the track and then looks to heave it away but misses. It bounces a little extra. It hits the shoulder of Buttler and goes to the off side. Masood is itching to get to his fifty it seems. There is no need to go for that shot after playing so well.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Tossed up on off, Masood defends it to point.
Floated delivery on leg, Azam flicks it to square leg.
Tossed up delivery on middle, Azam flicks it through mid-wicket for a single.
Loopy delivery on off, Masood defends it off the front foot.
Full delivery on off, Masood drives it through mid off for a run.
FOUR! Nicely swept! On middle, Azam sweeps it towards fine leg for a boundary.
Floated delivery on middle, Azam flicks it through mid-wicket for a single.
Floated on middle, Azam flicks it to square leg.
Quicker one on off, Azam defends it out onto the pitch.
FOUR! Excellent use of the feet from Azam! Tossed up ball on middle, Azam dances down the track and lifts it over mid on and into the fence.
Excellent batting! Short on middle, Babar tucks it to deep square leg for a single.
Loopy ball on middle, Masood defends it back to the bowler.
Flatter one outside off, Masood cuts it to point.
Excellent start from James Anderson! He bowls a good length ball on off, moving away. Azam looks to defend but the ball beats the outside edge, hits the thigh pad and rolls to the slip cordon.
On a length on middle, Azam stands tall and blocks it to cover. Azam wants the single but is sent back.
Another good length ball on off, Azam strides forward and blocks it to the cover region. Good first three deliveries from Anderson.
Anderson goes full this time and bowls it outside off, Babar lets it go to the keeper.
Fullish ball on middle, Babar solidly defends it to mid-wicket.

OUT! CAUGHT! That's what England would have been hoping for at the start! Brilliant delivery from James Anderson. Azam goes after playing a classy knock. England needed this start after having a poor Day 1. Anderson dishes a full delivery outside off, moving away. Azam looks to drive it. It takes the outside edge and goes to Root at first slip who makes no mistake. Anderson was testing Azam in this over and gave away no freebies and he has been rewarded for his tight line and length.
On a good length and outside off, Masood leaves it alone.

NOT OUT! There is bat involved! England lose a review! It did not look he had hit it but the replays prove otherwise! Broad bowls a good length ball on off, angling in. Masood looks to defend but seems to have missed. It raps him on his pads and England put up an appeal. The umpire is not interested. Root takes the review after a brief discussion with his teammates and opts for it. The Ultra Edge rolls in and it shows that there is a spike as the ball passed the bat. Great decision by the umpire.
Full delivery on middle, Masood flicks it to deep mid-wicket and picks up a couple.

FIFTY! 7th Test fifty for Masood! He struggled at the start but he stuck it out and now has reached his fifty. Brilliant. Back of a length ball outside off, Masood punches it through the cover region and picks up a couple to get to the milestone. Can he continue on and score a big one?
Outside off, left alone.
Length ball on middle, Masood defends it to mid-wicket.
Good length ball on middle, Shafiq flicks it to fine leg for a couple. Shafiq is off the mark.
Full ball on middle, Shafiq defends it back to the bowler.
Good length ball outside off, left alone.
FOUR! Beautiful from Shafiq! Full ball outside off, Shafiq leans forward and creams the drive through the cover region for a boundary.
Full ball on off, Shafiq looks to defend but it takes the outside edge and goes towards gully where the fielder stops it.
EDGY! Length ball outside off, Shafiq is late in getting his bat down. It takes the edge and goes towards second slip.
Good length ball outside off, Masood leaves it alone.
Full ball on middle, Shan plays it back to the bowler.
On middle, Masood pushes it to mid off.
Fullish outside off, Masood drives it crisply towards cover but for no runs as the fielder dives to make a good stop.
On a length on middle, Masood defends it back to the bowler.
Nicely bowled! Good length ball around off, nipping in. Masood attempts to defend it but misses out and gets hit on the pads.
Good length ball on off, Shafiq prods forward and defends it to the cover region.
Full on middle, Asad blocks it to mid on for a dot.
BEATEN! Anderson has been right on the money on Day 2. He was poor on Day 1. Good length ball outside off, Shafiq looks to defend but fails to get any bat on it.
On a length on off, Shafiq is solid in defense.
Good running! Length ball on off, Shafiq blocks it to cover and takes a quick single. Broad comes ahead and throws it to the keeper's end but misses. Masood was in though. 150 up for Pakistan.
Outside off, Masood does not bother playing at that.
Good length ball on middle, Shafiq strides forward and defends it to mid off.
Fullish on middle, Shafiq drives it straight to mid off.
Another full one on middle, Shafiq plays it back to the bowler.
Good length ball outside off, Shafiq leaves it alone.
On a length on off, Asad solidly blocks it to cover.
Good length delivery outside off, Shafiq watches the ball carefully and leaves it alone.
Outside off, left alone.
One more delivery outside off, Masood shoulders arms to this one.
Closer to the off pole but the length is shorter. Masood goes back and keeps it out easily.
Goes back to bowling outside off, another leave. Good carry for Anderson. Buttler takes it near his chest.
Fuller and on off, Masood strokes it to mid off.
One more delivery outside off, Masood does not fiddle with it.
Outside off, not played at.
On off, Shafiq lunges and keeps it out.
Good length delivery on the off pole, Shafiq gets right behind the line and keeps it out.
Slightly fuller this time and on off, Shafiq pushes it towards mid off.

OUT! EDGED AND TAKEN! Broad now gets one! Asad Shafiq walks back for a single digit score and England are probably back on top in this game. This is a lovely delivery. It is on a length, it lands around off and then straightens a touch. There is also good bounce on this one. Asad looks to defend but does so inside the line. It flies off the outside edge and goes towards second slip where Stokes makes no mistake. England have started brilliantly today morning.
A wicket maiden from Broad! Brilliant. On off, Rizwan defends it onto the ground.
Good length and on off, Masood defends it.
That is a gem! Beats the outside edge! It is on a length and around off, angles away late. Masood is drawn into playing at it. He ends up pushing at it away from the body. Gets beaten.
Wide outside off, left alone.
Once again keeps it outside off, it is not fiddled with.

Change of angle from Anderson and it nearly worked! Angles it into the off pole and then gets it to straighten. Masood is squared up as he tries to block. It goes off the outside edge but on the bounce to gully. Masood played it with soft hands.
A harmless delivery to end! Outside off, Masood shoulders arms to this one. Another maiden.
Watchful leave! This is just outside off, not played at.
Into the off pole now, Rizwan solidly keeps it out.
One more delivery outside off, not played at. There have been quite a few deliveries which have been outside off.

NOT OUT! There is a spike on Ultra Edge! Just a feather probably which only Rizwan must have felt and hence, he reviewed. A good one though and the Pakistan side will breathe a big sigh of relief. Another wicket would have been dreadful for them right now. Broad lands it on middle, it is on a length. Rizwan goes back to defend but it straightens. It seems to have missed the bat and hit the pad. An appeal and up goes the finger. Rizwan reviews immediately. Replays roll in and it shows the on-field call has to be overturned.
On the stumps, Rizwan gets right behind the line and defends it.
Once again makes the batter play by attacking the stumps. Rizwan negotiates it well. Good three balls to end.
Back of a length and on middle, kept out.
Outside off, Masood need not play at those.
One more ball outside off, Masood lets it go.
Shorter and on off, Masood guides it to point.
Very full and outside off, Anderson is looking to tempt Masood into a drive. The opener resists and lets it be.
Outside off again, left alone. Another maiden over. 6 in a row for England. Pakistan are playing themselves into a shell here.
BEATEN! Lovely bowling from Woakes! This was a loose shot though! Full delivery outside off, Rizwan pushes at it but fails to get any bat on it.
On a length on off, Mohammad blocks it to cover.
Fullish ball on off, Rizwan prods forward and blocks it to the off side. Pakistan last scored a run in the 54th over.
Fullish ball outside off, Rizwan shoulders arms to this one.
Finally, Pakistan have scored runs! Last time they scored in the 54th over. On a length on off, Rizwan guides it through the gully region  for a couple.
Good length ball on off, Rizwan pushes it through point and picks up another couple of runs.
Back of a length and on off, defended.

FOUR! Elegant! A boundary at last for Pakistan! This is full and outside off, Masood drives it square on the off side and it races away to the fence. He played it away from his body but the key was he was leaning into the stroke.
A single to follow the boundary! On off, it is pushed wide of mid off for one.
Good length and on middle, Rizwan keeps it out.
Another defensive stroke! This is played away from the body but this time it is done well. However, it is quite risky in England. You need to play it late and close to the body.
Another good over by Anderson comes to an end. On off, kept out.
Full ball on off, Masood pushes it through the cover region for a single.
Good length ball on off, Rizwan defends it to cover.
BEATEN! Good length ball outside off, Rizwan looks to defend but fails to get any bat on it.
Fullish on middle, Mohammad works it to mid-wicket.
On a length on middle, pushed back to the bowler.
Fullish on middle, Rizwan plays it towards mid on for nothing.
Length delivery on off, Masood punches it through point for a run.

BEATEN! Beauty of a delivery! On a good length on off, Rizwan looks to defend but misses it due to the inswing on this one. It went over the stumps towards the keeper where Buttler collects it safely.
On a length on off, Rizwan taps it to point.
Good length delivery on off, Rizwan blocks it off the front foot.
On a good length on middle, Rizwan offers a solid defense on this one.
Short delivery on middle, Rizwan drops it on the leg side and takes a quick single.
Good length ball on off, Rizwan pushes it to mid off.
Full delivery on middle, Mohammad drives it to mid on for another dot.
Good shot for nothing! Another full delivery on off, Rizwan drives it to mid off for nothing.
Outside off, not played at.
Good length ball on off, Rizwan drives it to mid off.
Good length ball on off, Mohammad strides forward and blocks it to cover.
Good length ball on middle, Masood defends it back to the bowler.
Short ball on middle, Shan pulls it to fine leg for a single.
Punched away! Good length ball outside off, Rizwan punches it through the covers and picks up three before the fielder cuts it off.
Good length ball outside off, Masood lets it through to the keeper.
On a length on middle, Masood blocks it to mid on.
Shan solidly defends this good length ball back to the bowler.
Full ball outside off, Rizwan lets it go to the keeper.
Back of a length on off, Rizwan camps on his back foot and defends it to the off side.
That came back in sharply! Length ball around off, angling in. Rizwan looks to flick but misses. An appeal is made for LBW but nothing from the umpire.
Fullish on middle, driven to mid on.
Good length ball on off, Mohammad blocks it to point.
On off, Rizwan prods forward and plays it to point.
Fullish on off, Masood blocks it to cover.
On a length on middle, Masood flicks it to square leg.
Short ball around off, Masood sways away from it.
Shortish on middle, Shan pulls it but it goes straight to mid-wicket.
BOUNCER! It is bowled around middle, Masood does well to duck under it.
Archer bends his back and bowls a short one on middle, Masood pulls it to deep square leg for a single.
FOUR! A handy gift for Pakistan! First real poor delivery from them on Day 2! Full ball on the pads, Masood flicks it to the fine leg region for a boundary.
Good length ball outside off, left alone.
The batsman lets the ball go outside his off stump.
An appeal for LBW! Good length ball on off, angling in. Masood looks to defend but gets hit on the pads. The players appeal but the umpire is not interested. They do not take the review.
Full on middle, Masood pushes it back to the bowler.
On middle, Shan flicks it wide of mid on for a single.
Good length ball on middle, Masood tucks it through the mid-wicket region for a couple.
On a length on off, Masood pushes it to point.
Good length ball on the pads, Masood flicks it to deep square leg for a single.
Back of a length on middle, Rizwan tucks it to deep square leg for a single.
BOUNCER! Short ball around middle, Masood ducks under it.
Full delivery on middle, Masood defends it back to the bowler.

OUT! CAUGHT! Pakistan have lost half their side! Rizwan was looking fidgety out there and he perishes! Beautiful piece of bowling from Woakes. He has been England's best bowler so far and he delivers yet again. Good length ball around off, Rizwan looks to defend but it goes off the outside edge towards the right of the keeper. Buttler tumbles and takes a simple catch. England have been all over Pakistan in the morning session of Day 2.
BEATEN! Just beautiful from Woakes! Good length ball outside off, Shadab looks to defend but fails to get any bat on it.

PLAY AND A MISS! Excellent stuff from Woakes! He is bowling on another level! Good length ball outside off, moving away. Khan looks to defend but fails to get any bat on it. Root seems excited and appeals but the umpire says no.
Back of a length ball outside off, Khan punches it to cover.
Full ball on middle, Khan pushes it to mid on.
Probably going down the leg side! Woakes bowls a full delivery on the pads, Shadab looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pads. An appeal for LBW is made but nothing from the umpire.
Good length ball on off, Masood looks to defend but it takes the inside edge and rolls to square leg.
Back of a length ball outside off, Masood punches it through the cover region for three.
PLAY AND A MISS! Khan has to be careful! He does not need to play at that! Short ball outside off, Shadab looks to cut but fails to get any bat on it.
BEATEN! That is a lovely delivery from Archer! Good length ball around off, moving away. Khan looks to defend but misses it completely.
On a length on off, Khan defends it to point. He wants the single but is sent back.
Full delivery on middle, Shadab pushes it to mid on for another dot ball.
Full on off, Masood solidly pushes it to mid off and shouts a loud no to his partner.
Back of a length ball on off, Shan punches it to cover.
Outside off, not played at.
EDGY FOUR! It is fortunate but Pakistan will take it! Full delivery on middle, Masood looks to flick but it takes the leading edge and goes past the gully fielder and into the fence.
BEATEN! Wow! This is some piece of bowling from Woakes! Good length ball outside off, Masood looks to defend but misses.
The batsman defends it from within the crease.
Full on middle, Khan pushes it to mid on.

Needed a direct hit! It was very close! Very full ball on middle, Shadab flicks it to mid-wicket and calls Masood for a single. Pope runs ahead and collects the ball, he has a shy at the keeper's end but misses.
Short ball on middle, Masood pulls it to deep square leg for a single.
Length ball on middle, Khan plays it to mid on.
BOUNCER! It is bowled around middle, Khan ducks under it.
Full delivery outside off, Khan leaves it alone.
Tossed up on middle, Masood plays it back to the bowler.
Loopy ball on off, Masood blocks it to point.
Flatter delivery outside off, Masood cuts it through the point region and picks up a couple before the fielder cuts it off.
Flat one on middle and leg, Masood looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pads.
Terrific spin there! Loopy ball on off, spinning away sharply. Masood prods forward to defend but misses as the ball turns away.
There is definitely some turn there! Floated outside off, Masood lets it go to the keeper. LUNCH ON DAY 2.
Pakistan are underway straightaway! Floated ball outside off, Shadab pushes it through the gully region and picks up three.
Loopy ball on middle, Masood defends it back to the bowler.
Short ball outside off, Shan punches it to cover for a single.
FOUR! Shadab has come out with intent! Flighted ball on the pads, Khan flicks it to the deep square leg region for a boundary.
Short and outside off, Khan cuts but straight to point.
Floated on middle, Shadab plays it back to the bowler.
Flatter one on off, Masood gets his bat down in time and guides it towards third man. A single taken.
Short ball on the pads, Shadab works it to square leg for a single.
Flatter one on off, Masood pushes it to the off side for a single.
FOUR! This is poor bowling from Bess! Just like yesterday, England have not started the post-Lunch session well! Short down the leg side, Khan helps it on its way to the fine leg boundary.
Another short one on the pads, Shadab pulls it to deep square leg for a single.
Floated on off, Masood defends it onto the pitch.
On the pads, Shadab works it to mid-wicket.
Tossed up on middle, Khan plays it back to the bowler.
Flatter one on the pads, Khan plays it to the deep square leg region for a single.
Full delivery on off, Masood drives it to mid off and takes a quick single.
The batsman defends it from within the crease.
Short ball on the pads, Khan looks to pull but it hits the pads and rolls to fine leg. A leg bye taken.
Looped up ball on middle, Khan defends it out.
Shortish on middle, Shadab bends on his knees and works it to deep square leg for a single.
Looped up ball on off, Masood defends it to silly point.
Full on middle, Masood blocks it back to Bess.
Quicker delivery on the pads, Masood tucks it to square leg and takes a single.
Tosses this one on middle, Khan defends it out back to the bowler.
Angled into the pads, it is worked through mid-wicket for one.
On middle, Khan lunges and keeps it out.
One more sweep by Shadab. He gets it through square leg for two.
Another couple! Shadab brings out the sweep again. Anything on the leg stump and even on the middle is being swept by him. He is playing it well. This is fine on the leg side for two.
Finds the fielder this time! One more sweep and this time it is connected really well but straight to square leg.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat. One run added to the total.
Broad starts with a good length ball around off, angling in. Khan blocks it solidly towards the cover region.
Short ball on middle, Shadab pulls it wide of mid on for a single.
Good length ball on off, Masood blocks it to cover off the front foot.
FOUR! Pakistan are scoring freely after Lunch! This is beautifully played! Good length ball on middle, Masood flicks it to the deep square leg region for a boundary.
Good length ball outside off, Masood lets it go to the keeper.
Outside off, left alone by Masood.
Outside off, it is left alone.
Just over the off pole! A poor shot by Shadab. It is shorter and outside off, cuts back in. Khan looks to cut but misses. It goes over the off pole. It also stayed low a touch.
Good length ball outside off, Khan shoulders arms to it.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground. They pick up a single.
BEATEN! The away-swinger from off, Masood is drawn into the stroke away from the body. He gets beaten.
One more delivery angling away from the off pole. Masood plays it late and guides it to gully.
Back of a length, angled into the batter. Khan looks to defend but it takes the inside edge, hits the pad and rolls on the leg side. A quick run.
Shorter and around off, Masood guides it towards point for one. Good run! The two are really playing well out there. Scoring freely and not letting the pressure build.
On middle, defended.
A quick run! Shorter and around off, it is tapped towards point for one.
Outside off, left alone.
Fuller and on off, it is driven towards mid off.
Good length ball on middle, Khan flicks it to deep square leg and picks up a couple.

Overthrows! Good length ball on off, Khan defends it to point and he wants the single but is sent back. The fielder comes ahead and has a shy at the keeper's end but misses. The ball goes towards deep square leg, allowing the batsmen to take two. 50-run stand is up between the two. Excellent one for Pakistan. They have been proactive after Lunch and they are looking good. They need to continue though.
On a length on off, Khan looks to defend but it takes the inside edge onto the pads.
FOUR! Poor bowling from Anderson! Rightly put away! Short and wide outside off, Khan hammers it through the point region for a boundary.
Good length ball on middle, Khan defends it back to the bowler.
Fullish on off, Khan prods forward and blocks it towards point. He wants the single but Masood sends him back.
FOUR! Masood is into the 90s! This is another good shot from him! Good length ball outside off, Masood guides it through the gully region for a boundary.
Full ball on middle, Masood defends it back to the bowler.
Good length ball outside off, Shan lets it go through to the keeper.
FOUR! Another one! Masood is inching closer and closer to his century! Good length ball outside off, Masood plays it towards the third man region for a boundary.
Length ball on the pads, Masood flicks it to deep square leg and picks up a couple. Moves to 98.
Full on middle, Masood pushes it to mid on.
Back of a length ball on middle, Khan works it to the leg side and takes a quick single.

CENTURY! There it is for Shan Masood! 4th Test century for him! It has been one kind of a knock. He weathered the early storm of Anderson and Broad on Day 1 and from thereon, he has not looked back. He enters an elite list of Pakistan players to score 3 centuries in consecutive innings. Full delivery on middle, Masood flicks it to deep mid-wicket for a couple. He removes his helmet and soaks in the applause from his teammates.
Full delivery on middle, Masood plays it back to the bowler.
BEATEN! Good length ball outside off, Masood looks to defend but fails to get any bat on it.
Outside off, left alone.
Good length ball outside off, Masood shoulders arms to it.
Good length ball outside off, Shadab leaves it alone.
Short ball outside off, Khan hops and looks to play it first but then decides to let it go.

Just short! Should Archer have gone for it? Short ball on middle, Khan looks to pull but it takes the top edge and goes towards fine leg. Archer comes forward but it falls short of him. A single taken.
Short ball on middle, Masood works it to deep square leg for a single.
Excellent delivery! Good length ball on off, angling in. Shadab looks to defend but it goes off the inside edge, hits the pads and rolls to the leg side. A single taken.
Full delivery on the pads, Masood flicks it to deep square leg and picks up a couple. Runs coming thick and fast for Pakistan now.
Good length ball on off, Khan pushes it to point and takes a single. 250 up for Pakistan.
Good length ball on middle, Masood flicks it to mid-wicket and takes off for a single. The fielder has a shy at the bowler's end but misses. Khan probably had made it with his dive.
Short ball on middle, Shadab pulls it to fine leg for a single.
Good length ball outside off, Masood leaves it alone.
Back of a length on off, Masood blocks it to cover.
FOUR! Nicely played! Good length ball outside off, Masood pushes it through the cover region. The fielder gives it a chase but the ball wins the race. A boundary signalled.
Woakes starts with a full ball on middle, Shadab works it to square leg for a single.
On a length on off, Masood blocks it to point.
Good length ball on middle, Masood gets behind the line of the delivery and blocks it back out onto the pitch.
Masood defends this length ball on off towards point.
Good length ball on middle, Masood works it towards square leg. Pope runs across and dives but fails to stop it. Two taken.
Good length ball on off, Masood defends it to the off side.
Floated on middle, Khan flicks it to mid-wicket.
Tossed up ball on off, Khan comes down the track and defends it to cover.
Flatter delivery outside off, Khan punches it towards cover for a single.
Floated on middle, Masood plays it back to the bowler.
Tossed up on middle, Masood drives it to mid on and picks up another run.
On middle, worked to mid-wicket.
Good length ball on middle, Masood works it to mid-wicket.
On a length on the pads, Shan tucks it to deep square leg and collects a single.
Another length ball on the pads, Khan nudges it to the leg side for a run.
Good length ball outside off, Masood leaves it alone.
Outside off, not played at.
Full ball on the pads, Masood flicks it to mid-wicket for a single.
Flatter one outside off, Masood pushes it to point.
Full toss on the pads, Masood comes down the track and looks to heave it away but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Tossed up on middle, Masood defends it back to the bowler.
Loopy ball on middle, Masood flicks it to mid-wicket for a single.
Well played! Floated ball outside off, Khan drives it through cover-point. The fielder chases after it but cannot stop the batsmen from taking three.
On middle, Masood blocks it back to the bowler.
Short ball down the leg side, Khan ducks under it.
Short ball on middle, it does not bounce as much after pitching. Khan still does very well to duck under it.
What is Khan doing there? Short ball around middle, Khan hops and looks to hammer it over the of side but fails to get any bat on it.
Another bouncer bowled around middle, Khan ducks under it.
BOUNCER! It is bowled around middle, Shadab ducks under it again.
Shortish down the leg side, Khan lets it go to the keeper.
FOUR! Beautifully swept away from Masood! Loopy ball on middle, Masood sweeps it to the fine leg region for a boundary.

FOUR! What a way to reach the 100-run partnership! Brilliant partnership for Pakistan! They have put Pakistan on top! Floated on off, Masood dances down the track and drives it through extra cover for a boundary.
Short ball outside off, Masood punches it to deep cover for a single.
Loopy on middle, flicked to mid-wicket.
On middle, Khan defends it back to the bowler.
Flatter one on middle, Shadab works it to square leg.
Good shot! Full ball outside off, Masood creams the drive through covers and picks up three before the fielder cuts it off.
Short ball on the pads, Khan pulls it to fine leg for a single.
Good length ball on middle, Masood flicks it to mid-wicket.
Length ball outside off, Shan lets it go to the keeper.
Full delivery on middle, Masood flicks it to square leg.
On a length on off, Masood blocks it to point.
Flatter one outside off, Shadab looks to cut but fails to get any bat on it.
Flatter one on middle, Khan works it to square leg.

OUT! CAUGHT! England needed that desperately! A brilliant partnership comes to an end! Shadab Khan played a handy innings but now has to walk back. Bess tosses this one on middle, Shadab comes down the track and looks to heave it to the mid-wicket. He does not get to the pitch of the ball and can only get a top edge. Joe Root settles himself and takes a simple catch. England need to keep taking wickets.
On middle, Masood defends it back to the bowler.
Quicker one outside off, Masood lets it go to the keeper.
Loopy ball on the pads, Masood looks to flick but gets hit on the pads.
On a good length on off, Shah blocks it off the front foot.
Good length delivery on middle, Yasir keeps it out.
Full delivery on off, Shah drives it through mid off. Broad gets a hand on it but does not stop the batters from taking two runs.
Woakes bowls a bouncer outside off, Yasir does well to duck under it.
Good length delivery outside off, Shah shoulders arms to this one.
Length delivery outside off, Shah taps it towards third man. The fielder chases it and does well to stop it just before the ropes. The batsmen get three runs.
Loopy delivery on middle, Shah blocks it off the front foot.
Flighted delivery on off, Yasir defends it out.
BEATEN! Floated ball outside off, Shah looks to defend but misses it.
Floated delivery on middle, Shah flicks it towards the leg side.

Is that a drop? From the reactions of Dom Bess, it looks like it. Floated ball outside off, Shah prods forward to defend but he seems to have missed it. Buttler fails to collect it as well. Ohh no, the replays show that there was bat on it. Then, it was a dropped catch. Buttler is having a tough time in the field. Two dropped catches and 1 missed stumping so far.
On middle, Yasir flicks it towards the leg side.
On a good length on off, Masood defends it off the back foot.
Good length delivery on off, Shan keeps it out.
On a good length on middle, Masood defends it out.
Good length delivery on off, Shan blocks it off the back foot.
Length delivery down the leg side, Masood leaves it alone.
On a good length on off, Masood keeps it out.
Flighted delivery on middle, Shah flicks it towards the leg side.
Tossed up delivery on off, Yasir blocks it off the front foot.
On middle, Shah flicks it towards short leg.
Loopy delivery on off, Yasir blocks it off the front foot.
Floated delivery on middle, Shah defends it out.
On off, Yasir offers a solid defense on this one.
Good length ball on the pads, Masood looks to flick but gets hit on the thigh pad.
Down the leg side, Masood looks to flick but misses.
Good length ball on middle, Masood defends it back to the bowler.
Short ball on middle, Masood pulls it to deep square leg for a couple.
Shortish on middle, Masood pulls it to the deep mid-wicket region and collects a single.
Full ball on off, Shah defends it to point.
Flatter one outside off, Shan cuts it to deep point for a single.
EDGY! Flatter one on off, Shah looks to defend but it takes the edge and it goes towards gully.
Loopy ball on middle, Shah defends it back to the bowler.
On middle, Shah blocks it out.
Shorter outside off, Yasir punches it to point.
Floated on middle, Shah blocks it back to the bowler.
On a good length on off, Masood flicks it towards fine leg for a single.

OUT! LBW! Time up and Shah cannot take the review! Archer gets his second wicket. Good length ball on middle and leg, nipping in. Shah looks to defend but misses and gets rapped on the pads. Archer and the rest appeal and the umpire raises his finger. Yasir is involved in a long discussion with Masood but the time finishes. He has to walk back to the pavilion. The Ball Tracker rolls in and it shows that it was umpire's call on hitting the stumps. England three wickets away from bowling Pakistan out.

OUT! CAUGHT! Archer has two-in-two! He will be on a Hat-Trick. Pakistan's lower order is a little weak and it is proving correct. Good length ball around off, Abbas looks to defend but it takes the outside edge and goes to Root at first slip who pouches it comfortably. Pakistan collapsing yet again.
Plays out the Hat-Trick ball well! Back of a length ball on middle, Afridi solidly blocks it to mid-wicket.
NASTY! Short ball around middle, Shaheen looks to sway away from it. It hits his gloves and rolls to the slip cordon.
Very full delivery on middle, Afridi defends it back to the bowler.
SIX! Excellent batting! We might just see him up the ante! Floated ball on middle, Masood powers it over deep mid-wicket for a biggie. His first one of the game.
EDGY! Short ball outside off, Masood looks to cut but it takes the inside edge and onto the pads.
SIX! 300 up in some style! Loopy ball on middle, Masood dances down the track and hammers it over the bowler's head for another biggie.
Got his leg back in! Floated ball outside off, Masood moves to the off side and looks to heave it to the off side but misses. Buttler whips the bails off but Masood was in.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
FOUR! Just a four this time! Floated on middle, Masood thrashes it over mid on and into the fence. Good over for Pakistan.

An appeal for caught behind turned down! Good length ball outside off, Afridi looks to push but seems to have missed it. Archer appeals but nothing from the umpire. Root thinks of the review but decides against it and rightly so as the Ultra Edge shows no bat.
That's the one that Pakistan need! Full ball on off, Afridi drives it to cover and collects a single.
Short ball on middle, Masood pulls it to mid-wicket for another single.
Short ball on middle, Afridi hops and defends it onto the pitch.
Back of a length ball on off, Afridi blocks it towards point.
Good length ball outside off, Afridi leaves it alone.
Good length ball on off, Masood pushes it to mid off.

150 FOR MASOOD! What an innings from him! He has played really well and has been the backbone in this innings. Full ball on middle, Masood flicks it to deep square leg and calls Afridi for the second. The fielder throws it to Buttler. Afridi is slow off the blocks but makes his way in at the bowler's end as Buttler's throw is wide.
Fullish on middle, Masood flicks it to mid-wicket.
That is nasty! Short ball on middle, Masood looks to pull but is early into the shot. He misses and gets hit on the elbow.
Sloppy from England! Short ball on middle, Masood pulls it to fine leg. Anderson comes across but allows the ball to go past him. Two taken.
Nicely bowled! Good length ball on off, angling in. Shaheen looks to defend but misses and gets hit on the pads. TEA ON DAY 1.
Good length ball on middle, Masood tucks it to square leg.
Short ball on middle, Masood pulls it to deep mid-wicket and refuses the single.
FOUR! Poor stuff from Archer! Cannot bowl there at all! Short ball on the pads, Masood pulls it fine to the fine leg region for a boundary.
Shortish around middle, Shan pulls it to deep square leg and takes a single this time.
Good length ball on the pads, Afridi flicks it to fine leg but does not take the single.

An appeal for LBW turned down! Good length ball on the pads, Afridi looks to defend but misses. Archer and England appeal but nothing from the umpire. They do not take the review. The Ball Tracker rolls in and it shows that it is missing leg stump.

OUT! LBW! Umpire's call it is and Masood's magnificent innings comes to an end. Brilliant stuff. He has taken Pakistan to a strong position. He raises his bat as he walks back to the dressing room. Good length ball on middle, angling in. Masood looks to push but misses and gets rapped on the pads. Broad appeals and the umpire raises the finger. Broad appeals and the umpire takes a lot of time to raise his finger. Broad does not realize that he has given it out and is surprised as he turns around to have a look at the umpire again. Masood reviews immediately. The Ultra Edge shows no bat while the Ball Tracker shows that it is umpire's call on hitting the stumps.
BEATEN! Lovely! Good length ball outside off, Shah looks to defend but fails to get any bat on it.
Short ball around middle, Shah ducks under it.
Good length ball down the leg side, Shah looks to flick but misses.
The batsman defends it from within the crease.
Full on middle, Shah plays it back to the bowler.
NO BALL! Archer oversteps! Full ball on middle, Shaheen drives it to mid on. The on-field umpire calls a No Ball and then realizes that it is the decision of the third umpire to call for it.
Very full delivery on off, Afridi defends it to cover.
Good length ball on middle and leg, Afridi blocks it to mid on.
Short ball around middle, Afridi ducks under it.
FOUR! Poor bowling from Archer! It had to be put away and it was. Slower full toss on the pads, Afridi flicks it to the deep square leg region for a boundary.
FOUR! That is timed beautifully from Afridi! Very full delivery on the pads, Afridi just pushes it to the deep square leg region for another boundary. Valuable runs for Pakistan.
Good length ball on middle, Afridi plays it back to the bowler.
Short ball down the leg side. Naseem looks to flick but misses.
Another one down the leg side, Shah looks to put bat on ball again but misses it altogether.

OUT! CAUGHT! That's the end of that! Clear spike on Ultra Edge and Pakistan's innings is over. Good length ball around off, Shah looks to defend but it seems to have hit the gloves and goes into the mitts of the keeper. They appeal and the umpire raises his finger. Shah does not think that he is out and reviews. The Ultra Edge shows that there is a spike as the ball passes the gloves. PAKISTAN BOWLED OUT FOR 326.
Afridi starts with a poor one! Good length ball down the leg side, Burns lets it go to the keeper.
Excellent follow-up delivery from Afridi! Good length ball outside off, moving away. Burns lets it go to the keeper.
FOUR! ENGLAND ARE UNDERWAY IN A TERRIFIC FASHION! Afridi overpitches it on middle, Burns flicks it nonchalantly through mid-wicket for a boundary.

OUT! LBW! Fantastic review from Pakistan! What a start for them! Just the start they needed! That's why Pakistan's fast bowling line-up is one of the best. Good length ball on middle and leg, which straightens after pitching. Burns looks to push but misses and gets rapped on the pads. Pakistan put in a huge appeal but nothing from the umpire. Azhar takes the review after consulting his teammates. The Ultra Edge shows no bat and the Ball Tracker shows that it is pitching in line, impact is in line and is hitting the stumps. Burns fails and this is a terrible start for England.
Full ball outside off, Root lets it go through to the keeper.
Good length ball outside off, Root leaves it alone. Excellent start from Pakistan.
Length and just outside off, left alone.
Good delivery! On a length and around off, shapes away a touch. Sibley defends it out nicely.
Outside off, it is left alone.
On middle, it is worked through square leg for two. Sibley is off the mark.
On off, defended.
EDGY FOUR! Fuller and around middle, it shapes away. Sibley looks to play it with a straight bat but it goes off the outside edge wide of gully for a boundary.
OHH! Good shape and carry for Afridi! Good length ball outside off, angling in sharply. Root watches the ball carefully and shoulders arms.

NOT OUT! Excellent review from Joe Root! Afridi gets a lot of bounce due to his height and that's what saved the English skipper. Afridi is on fire at the moment! He is causing all sorts of problems for England. Good length ball around off, nipping in sharply, Root is late into his defense and gets hit on the pads. Afridi and the rest appeal and the umpire raises the dreaded finger. Root takes the review immediately. The Ultra Edge confirms that there is no bat on it. What about Ball Tracker? It shows that it is missing the stumps.

Another appeal! An inside edge saves Root! Full delivery on middle and leg, Root looks to flick but seems to have inside edged it onto the pads. Afridi goes up in huge appeal but nothing from the umpire. The replays confirm that there is an edge on that.
Full ball on off, Root pushes it to cover.
Good length ball on middle, Root blocks it solidly.
On a length on off, Root defends it out onto the pitch.
On a length on middle, Sibley flicks it through square leg. The batsmen get two runs.

OUT! Three reds and that turns out to be a waste of a review. Expected that as it looked plumb. England in deep, deep trouble here as they have lost both their openers within the first 4 overs. Abbas has one now. This is on a length and around off, it pitches and jags back in. Sibley fails to put bat on ball and is hit on the pad. An appeal and up goes the finger. Sibley reviews and replays show that the on-field call is the right one. England lose a review too.
Good length and on middle, defended.
On off, it is defended again. Stokes is standing well ahead of his crease to negotiate the swing.
Another solid defense to this ball on middle.
A wicket maiden! On middle, Stokes keeps it out.
Full delivery way outside off, Root does not bother playing at that one.
Good length ball outside off, Root lets it through to the keeper.
On a length on off, Root solidly blocks it to point.
Short ball outside off, Root sways away from it.
Good length ball on off, angling in. Root strides forward and blocks it to mid off.
Good length ball on middle, Root defends it back to the bowler.
Good length ball outside off, Stokes leaves it alone.
Full ball on off, Stokes prods forward and blocks it to cover.

OUT! TIMBER! It takes something special to get Stokes out and this is one of the best balls you will get to see. You could see the surprise on Stokes' face. Unplayable to be honest. Stokes standing in the crease or outside wouldn't have mattered. One just gets the feeling that delivery would have gotten out many batters. It is a length delivery, slightly fuller for Stokes as he is a touch ahead of his crease. He looks to defend the original trajectory but the ball moves away and hits the top of off. Pakistan are ecstatic. They know the importance of this wicket. Waqar Younis, the bowling coach, is a pleased man as he applauds from the pavilion. Abbas would have enjoyed it as that is what you hope of, hitting the top of off as a bowler. Pakistan all over England at the moment. Mohammad Abbas just showing once again what he is capable of in England. Top class stuff.
On a length on off, Pope pushes it to point.
EDGY FOUR! Unconvincing but England will take it! Good length ball on off, Pope looks to defend but it takes the edge and goes through the gully region for a boundary.
Good length ball on middle, Pope flicks it to mid-wicket. The third umpire checks for a No Ball but is fine. End of another excellent over.
Full ball on off, Root pushes it to point.
Full on off, Root drives it to mid off.
Good length ball outside off, Root lets the ball through to the keeper.
Good length ball outside off, left alone.
Full ball on middle, Root works it to square leg.
Fullish ball on off, Root blocks it to cover.
Good length ball on middle, Pope pushes it to mid on.
Well played! Good length ball outside off, Pope guides it through gully and picks up a couple.
Full ball on off, Pope pushes it to cover and takes a single.
Nicely bowled! Good length ball, nipping in. Root looks to defend but misses and gets hit high on the pads.
Finally, Root is off the mark! It took him 22 balls to do so. Fullish on off, Root plays it to cover and takes a single.
Good length ball on off, Pope guides it to gully.
Good length ball outside off, Root shoulders arms to it.
NO BALL! Very full delivery on middle, Root plays it well as he defends it to the off side. Afridi has overstepped.
BEATEN! Lovely stuff from Afridi! Good length ball outside off, Root looks to defend but fails to get any bat on it.
Full on middle, Root pushes it to mid on.
BEATEN! Excellent piece of bowling from Afridi! Good length ball outside off, Root attempts to defend but fails to get any bat on it.
Outside off, left alone.
BEATEN! Afridi is on fire at the moment! Root is under a lot of pressure! Full delivery outside off, moving away. Root looks to block but fails to get any bat on it.
Good length ball on off, Pope defends it to cover.
Fullish on off, Pope looks to push it off the front foot but it takes the inside edge and goes towards the leg side.
On middle, Ollie pushes it down to mid on.
NO BALL! Abbas has overstepped! Good length ball on off, Ollie blocks it to the off side.
NO BALL! Length ball on off, Pope guides it to the gully region. Abbas oversteps again.
Full ball on middle, Pope flicks it through mid-wicket and picks up three before the fielder cuts it off.
On a length on off, Root blocks it out.
The batsman has played it to the point region.
Good length ball outside off, left alone.
On a length outside off, Pope does not bother to play at that one.
Full ball outside off, Pope lets it go to the keeper.
Fullish on middle, Pope pushes it back to the bowler.
Good shot for nothing! Full delivery on middle, Pope drives it straight back. It touches the boot of Afridi and rolls to the stumps at the bowler's end.
Nicely done! Full delivery outside off, Pope drives it through covers and picks up a couple to end the over.
Good length ball on middle, Root plays it back to the bowler.
On a length outside off, Root has no problems in leaving it alone.
Good length ball on off, Root strides forward and defends it to cover.
Length ball on middle, Root flicks it to square leg.
Good length ball outside off, Root shoulders arms to it.
Good length ball on off, Root looks to defend but it takes the inside edge and it goes towards deep square leg. A couple taken.
Shah starts with a good length ball outside off, at 136 kph. Pope lets it go to the keeper.
That took off! Good length ball outside off, that takes off after pitching. Pope leaves it alone. Rizwan does well to collect it.

BIG SHOUT! Good length ball on middle and leg, Pope looks to flick but gets hit on the pads. There is a huge appeal for LBW but nothing from the umpire. The Ball Tracker shows that it is missing the stumps.
Full on off, Pope pushes it to mid off.
Good length ball on middle, Pope looks to flick but misses and hits him on the pads. The ball rolls to square leg and the batters take a leg bye.
BEATEN! Excellent start from Naseem! Good length ball outside off, Root looks to defend but fails to get any bat on it.
Full ball on middle, Pope pushes it to mid on for nothing.
On a length on the pads, Pope flicks it through mid-wicket and picks up a single.
Good length ball on middle, Root is solid in defense.
On a length on off, Joe punches it to cover.
Good length ball outside off, Root shoulders arms to it.
On middle, solidly defended to silly mid off.
On a length on middle at 143 kph. Pope solidly plays it back to the bowler.
Full ball on middle, Ollie pushes it to mid on.
Good length ball down the leg side, Pope looks to flick but fails to make any connection.
FOUR! Classic shot from Pope! Brilliant! Full ball on middle, Pope drives it through mid on for a boundary.
Good length ball on middle, Pope flicks it to mid-wicket for a single.
On a length on middle and leg, Root defends it to mid on.
Shah starts with a loosener on the pads, Pope pulls it to deep square leg for a couple.
Loopy ball on off, Pope drives it through the covers for a single.

A big appeal for LBW! Probably going down leg. Floated ball on the pads, Root looks to defend but gets rapped on the pads. Pakistan appeal but the umpire is not interested. The Ball Tracker shows that it was pitching outside leg.
Massive turn! Loopy ball outside off, Root looks to defend but the ball spins away and beats the bat.
The batsman shoulders arms to let that one through.
FOUR! That will break the shackles! Loopy ball on middle, Root goes on his knees and then sweeps it to the deep square leg region for a boundary.
FOUR! Pope is a class player and it shows in this shot! Full delivery outside off, Pope lunges forward and drives it through the cover region for a boundary.
Good length ball on middle, Pope works it to mid-wicket.
On a length on off, Root blocks it to cover off the back foot.
Full ball on off, Root strides forward and plays it to mid off.
Short ball outside off, at 144 kph. Root looks to play at it first but moves his bat away.
Back of a length on off, Root blocks it to point.
Flatter ball outside off, Pope cuts it straight to point.
FOUR! Hammered! 50 up in style! Short ball on middle, Pope moves inside the crease and then pulls it to the deep square leg region for a boundary.
Good batting! Floated ball on middle, Pope comes down the track and flicks it to deep mid-wicket for a single.
Tossed up outside off, Root leaves it alone.
Short one outside off, Joe punches it to point.
FOUR! Yasir Shah is leaking runs here! Floated on middle, Root paddle sweeps it to the fine leg region for a boundary.
Short ball outside off, Pope sways away from it.
Good length ball on middle, Pope pushes it to mid on.
Length ball on off, Pope blocks it to cover off the front foot.
On a length on off, Ollie solidly blocks it to mid off.
PLAY AND A MISS! Extra effort ball from Naseem! Short ball outside off, Pope looks to play the cut but the ball beats the bat and goes into the mitts of the keeper.

An appeal for LBW! Good length ball on off, angling in. Pope looks to leave it but the ball comes in and hits him on the pads. Naseem appeals but nothing from the umpire. Good decision not to review as the Ball Tracker shows that it was missing the stumps.
Tossed up delivery on middle, Root flicks it through square leg. The batsmen get two runs.
Flighted delivery on off, Root looks to drive but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Floated delivery on off, Root plays it towards point. The batsmen cross ends.

Short and outside off, Pope cuts it through point for a single. 50-run partnership between Pope and Root. A much-needed partnership for England. They were in trouble early on and this has settled the nerves a little bit.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Root falls and Pakistan strike again! Yasir Shah did not start well but has delivered the wicket. Root was struggling at the crease and his luck runs out. Brilliant catch from Rizwan though. Flatter one around off, Root looks to cut but it is too close. It takes the outside edge towards the keeper. Rizwan takes a good catch. England have a long tail and they desperately did not want this wicket to fall. Pakistan are on top at the moment.
Loopy ball on middle, Buttler defends it back to the bowler.
On a good length on off, Pope defends it off the back foot.
Good length delivery on middle, Pope offers a solid block on this one.
Short delivery outside off, Pope sways away from it.
FOUR! Pope is a good player and shows it again. Short delivery on off, Pope pulls it through mid-wicket for a boundary.

FOUR! Slashes and slashes hard! There is a good battle going on between Naseem and Pope. Full ball outside off, Pope looks to slash but it takes the edge and goes past the gully fielder and into the fence.
Good length ball on off, Pope defends it out.
Loopy ball on off, Buttler prods forward and defends it to cover.
Low full toss on off, Buttler drives it to cover. It ricochets off the fielder towards mid off. No run though.
On middle, Buttler defends it back to the bowler.
Flighted ball on middle, Buttler paddle sweeps it to fine leg for a couple. Buttler is off the mark.
Low full toss on middle, Jos paddles it to fine leg for another couple.
Flatter one outside off, Buttler lets it go to the keeper.
Good length ball on the pads, Pope looks to defend. It goes off his thigh pad towards deep square leg. A leg bye taken.
Good length ball down the leg side, Buttler looks to flick but misses.
Good length ball outside off, Buttler leaves it alone.
Fullish ball outside off, Buttler does not play at that one.
Outside off, not played at.
FOUR! That's a poor delivery and it is beautifully played by Jos Buttler! Fullish on off, Buttler creams the drive through mid off for a boundary.
Flatter on middle, Pope flicks it to deep square leg and picks up a couple.
Loopy ball outside off, Pope shoulders arms to it.
Full on off, Pope dances down the track and drives it to mid off for a quick single.
Close! Floated outside off, Buttler looks to leave. The ball goes just past the off stump.
That nearly took the off stump! Loopy ball on middle, Buttler looks to defend but it spins away and beats the edge. It goes just over the off stump.
The batsman plays it with an angled bat and guides it to third man. The batsmen have run through for a single.
Good length ball outside off, Buttler shoulders arms to it.
Outside off, not played at.
On a length outside off, Buttler makes another leave to the keeper.
Good length delivery on middle, Jos blocks it to mid on.
On a length on the pads, Buttler looks to flick but gets hit on the pads. There is a mild appeal for LBW but nothing from the umpire.
Good length ball on middle, Buttler tucks it to mid-wicket.
Floated on middle, Pope defends it to short leg.
Flatter ball outside off, Pope lets it go to the keeper.
Tosses this one on middle, Pope uses his feet and drives it to mid off for a single.
FOUR! That is exceptionally well timed! Flatter one outside off, Buttler moves inside his crease and drives it through the cover region for a boundary.
This time behind square! Short ball outside off, Buttler cuts it behind square on the off side and picks up a couple.
Outside off, not played at.
Very full delivery outside off, Pope lets it go to the keeper.
Good length ball outside off, Ollie leaves it alone.
On a length on off, Pope defends it to mid off.
Good length ball on off, Ollie pushes it to cover and takes a single.
