Good shot for nothing! Full delivery on middle, Buttler drives it with power but straight back to the bowler.
Good length ball on off, Buttler blocks it to point.
Tossed up delivery on middle, Pope defends it off the back foot.
Flighted delivery on off, Pope plays it to covers.
Loopy delivery on off, Pope pushes it to point.

NOT OUT! Buttler is well in! The umpire probably wanted to be sure! Floated ball on middle, Pope comes down the track and pushes it back to the bowler. Shah gets a hand on it and it rolls onto the stumps. Pakistan appeal and the umpire takes it upstairs. The replays roll in and they show that Buttler was well in.
Flatter one on middle, Pope flicks it to deep square leg for a single.
Flighted outside off, Buttler leaves it alone. STUMPS ON DAY 2.
Afridi starts with a good length ball down the leg side, Pope leaves it alone.
Good length ball on off, angling in. Pope camps on his back foot and pushes it to gully.
Full ball on off, Pope prods forward and pushes it to the mid off region for a dot.
NO BALL! Shaheen oversteps! Good length on off, Pope solidly blocks it to cover.
Good length ball on middle, Pope flicks it to mid-wicket.
Another length ball outside off, Pope shoulders arms to it.
Good start from Afridi! Good length ball on off, Ollie pushes it to mid off to get through the over.
Abbas starts with an out-swinging good length delivery outside off, Buttler leaves it alone.
Good length ball on middle, Buttler solidly defends it to mid on.
Good length ball outside off, moving away. Buttler lets it through to the keeper.
Full ball on off, Buttler prods forward and defends it to cover.
On a length outside off, Buttler makes a leave to this one.
Good length ball on middle, Buttler solidly blocks it to mid-wicket.
Just outside off, Afridi is looking to get the ball back in. It goes on with the angle. Left alone.
Another leave as it is once again bowled outside off.

Quick run! Afridi gets this one full and around off, Pope pushes it to mid off and takes off. The fielder does have a shy at the bowler's end but misses. Pope's dive would have saved him though. The batsmen cross ends.
Another delivery on a length and on the stumps, defended nicely.
Once again hits the length and the off stump is attacked. Buttler goes back and keeps it solidly.
This one comes back in just a little after landing on middle, Buttler works it to mid-wicket.
Pope probably misses out on one there! It is angled into the pads, Pope works it nicely but too close to mid on for one.
Good length and on middle, kept out.
Outside off, left alone.

BEATEN! This is what Abbas can do. He would land it on a length and the line is around that off pole and get it to move both the ways. This time he gets it to straighten. Buttler does nothing wrong as he tries to play the original line but is beaten.
Outside off, not played at.
A fuller ball to end! JB strokes it towards mid on. The fielder there moves to his left quickly and stops it. Good energy shown by Pakistan in the field. They aren't letting England score easily.
Another dot! Fuller and around off, Pope looks to hit it through the off side but it goes off the inner half towards mid on.

It bounces over the stumps! Pope probably decided to play that really late and that could have cost him. It is on a length and just outside off. Pope looks to play it late but gets an inside edge which bounces in front of the stumps and then goes over it.

FIFTY FOR POPE! His 5th in Tests! Quality, quality knock till now! He thrived under testing conditions yesterday against bowlers who were brilliant. Also, he was under pressure when he walked out but he has come good. Needs to keep going though. He gets there by working it through square leg and bags a couple.
Fuller and outside off, Pope goes after it a little too hard. He gets an inside edge onto the leg side. Afridi has overstepped as the third umpire conveys the message to the on-field umpire.
Good length and on off, blocked.
Outside off, left alone.
The sucker ball to end, full and wide outside off. Pope is not sucked into the shot. He leaves it alone.
EDGED BUT JUST SHORT! Good length ball on off, Buttler looks to defend but gets an outside edge. Luckily for him, it lands short of the second slip fielder.

FOUR BYES! Poor keeping from Rizwan! Should have stopped that! Good length ball outside off, Buttler looks to defend but misses. The keeper fails to collect and the ball goes to the third man fence. 100 up.
On a length on off, Buttler blocks it to cover.
Fullish ball on off, Jos pushes it to mid off for another dot.
On a length outside off, Buttler does not bother playing at that one.
Outside off, not played at.
Another inside edge! Maybe Pope is just going at it a little too hard. It is full and outside off, Pope looks to hit it through the off side but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Fuller and on off, it tails back in a touch. Pope strokes it to mid on.

Good stop! Good work from Pakistan in the field! They are making England work hard for their runs which will just keep building the pressure. Full and on off, Pope strokes it to the right of mid off where the fielder dives and stops it.
Outside off, left alone.
Good running! Such quick singles are important when runs are not coming easily. On middle, it is pushed towards mid on for one.
On middle, Buttler defends it out nicely.
Outside off, not played at.
Just outside off, Pope does not play at it.
Attacks the off pole, blocked out.
One more delivery outside off, not played at.
Another one outside off, left alone.
On the stumps to end, defended nicely.
Naseem starts with a full delivery on off, at 142 kph. Buttler strides forward and pushes it to mid off.
Good length ball outside off, Buttler has no problems in leaving it alone.

Just short! The first slip fielder is standing a little behind! This though is a loose shot from Jos Buttler! Back of a length ball outside off, Buttler looks to punch it off the back foot but it takes the edge and goes towards first slip. It lands in front of the fielder at first slip.
Fullish delivery on off, Buttler prods forward and pushes it to cover.
Nice looking drive! Full ball outside off, Buttler leans forward and creams the drive through extra cover. Three taken before the fielder cuts it off. First runs for Jos in 30 balls.
That's a loose, loose shot from Pope! He would be disappointed by that! Good length ball outside off, Pope looks to drive but fails to make any connection with it.
Angled into the off pole, it pitches and then leaves the batter. Beats the outside edge of Buttler's bat. Good delivery again.

That is a peach! Just too good! Buttler could only hope for it to miss the outside edge. It lands on off and it is on a length which means Buttler has to play at it. He looks to defend but the ball leaves him and whizzes past the outside edge.
Angled into the pads, Buttler looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pads.
On middle, it is kept out. The umpire just having a look at where Abbas finishes with his followthrough, whether he is stepping on the danger area, no warning or word for now.
Goes wide of the crease now, maybe to create an angle or to stay away from the danger zone. It is outside off, left alone.
BEATEN AGAIN! Top, top stuff from Abbas! On a length and around off, it pitches and moves away. Buttler looks to defend but gets beaten.
Good length ball on off, Pope defends it to the cover region.
Top class stuff from Naseem! Pakistan have done well with the ball in the morning session! Good length ball outside off, Pope looks to defend but fails to get any bat on it.
On a length on middle, Pope works it to mid-wicket.
BEATEN! Wow, what a beauty from Naseem! There is a good battle going on between Naseem and Pope! Length ball outside off, Pope looks to defend but misses it completely.
Outside off, left alone by Pope.
Good length ball outside off, Pope leaves it alone.
Good length ball on middle, Buttler blocks it to cover off the back foot.
Abbas bowls a length ball outside off, Buttler covers his stumps and lets it go to the keeper.
On a length on off, Jos blocks it to point for another dot.
Goes full this time and bowls it on off, Jos strides forward and drives it to mid off.
FOUR BYES! The keeper is not getting that! A big in-swinger from Abbas on the pads, Buttler looks to flick but misses. Rizwan dives to his left but misses. The ball goes into the fine leg fence.
On off, Buttler solidly blocks it out onto the pitch.
Full delivery on middle, Pope flicks it to deep square leg for a single.
Good length ball outside off, Buttler shoulders arms to it.
On a length outside off, Buttler makes another leave.
Good length ball on off, Jos defends it to cover.
Fullish on middle, Jos taps it to the point region.
Good length ball outside off, Jos lets it go to the keeper.
BEATEN! Lovely delivery from Abbas! Good length ball outside off, Pope looks to push at it but fails to make any connection.
On a length on off, solidly blocked to mid off.
Good length ball on off, Pope blocks it to cover.
On a length outside off, Pope lets it go to the keeper.

Was there an edge? The keeper certainly thinks so. Good length ball outside off, Pope attempts to defend but misses. The keeper does well to collect it and appeals for caught behind. Nothing from the umpire though.
Fullish on off, Pope pushes it to point.
Full ball on middle and leg, Buttler blocks it to mid on.

FOUR! That is a gorgeous shot! That will give him a lot of confidence! Full delivery outside off, Buttler lunges forward and times it beautifully through extra cover for a boundary. 50-run stand comes up between the two. Brilliant one for the hosts. They have weathered the first hour well and need to continue.
Good length ball on middle, pushed back to the bowler.
On a length outside off, Buttler shoulders arms to it.
Outside off, not played at it again.
Good length ball outside off, Jos makes another leave.
On a length on middle, Pope works it to square leg.
NO BALL! Full ball on off, Pope pushes it towards cover-point and takes a single. The third umpire conveys it to the on-field umpire that Abbas has overstepped.
Good length ball on off, Buttler blocks it to cover.
Full ball outside off, Buttler lets it go to the keeper. Rizwan dives to his right and collects it well. Excellent keeping.
Quick single! Full delivery on middle,  Buttler works it to mid on and takes a single.
FOUR! Width and dealt with ease! Good length ball outside off, Pope drives it with superb timing through the cover region for a boundary.
On a length on off, Pope pushes it to point and takes off for a run. Buttler hesitates but decides to go for it. They make it easily in the end.
FOUR! Delightful! Easy! Full and outside off, Pope leans into it and creams it through covers for a boundary.
Drags his length back and the line is a little straighter. It is worked towards mid-wicket.

OUT! EDGED AND TAKEN! That is a nasty delivery! Top class from Naseem Shah. Pope is in disbelief! He couldn't do a lot over there. Needed something good to get rid of Pope who was looking solid and Shah has provided it. He is absolutely pumped up. A real effort ball. It lands on a length and around off, takes off from nowhere. Pope does all he could to keep it down. He looks to play it with soft hands and also tries taking one hand off the handle in the end. Nothing saves him as the ball keeps rising, hits the shoulder of the bat and lobs towards gully. Shadab takes it quite awkwardly. He had his body weight backwards but did well to hang onto it. He then indicates he did not see it. An important catch though as the momentum had just about started to shift. England trail by 199.
Good length and on off, kept out.
Back of a length and on middle, defended nicely.

Right on the helmet! Welcome to the crease Woakes! This is shorter and on middle, Woakes is a touch late in ducking under it. He is hit on the helmet. Seems a little rattled as he stays in the ducked position for a bit but seems fine now. End of a steamy over from Naseem.
Good length and on middle, defended.
Uppish but for two! Fuller and around off, Buttler plays a check-drive, it goes wide of the bowler and down towards long off for two.
Outside off, left alone.

WIDE! Way too short and well outside off, Buttler leaves. It keeps going with the angle after it passes the batter. Rizwan does well to move to his right and take it with one hand diving to that direction.
Closer to the off pole but not close enough to make the batter play.
One more ball outside off, it is not played at.
The batsman chooses to leave the ball outside his off stump.

That is a gem! But Chris Woakes seemed like he was actually backing away before the ball was even bowled. Maybe he was worried about another short ball. Shah though lands it on a length and around off, it pitches and straightens. Woakes ends up pushing at it tentatively away from his body. Gets beaten.
SHOT! This should give him some confidence. Another length delivery on off, Woakes strokes it on the up through covers and takes three.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
FOUR! Away from the body but gets the desired result! Fuller and outside off, tailing away. Buttler reaches out for it. It goes uppishly but wide of point and for a boundary.
Good length and outside off, not played at.
On middle, defended nicely.

An appeal for LBW turned down! Probably going down leg! Good length ball on middle and leg, angling in. Woakes looks to flick but misses and gets hit on the pad. There is an appeal for LBW but nothing from the umpire. Pakistan think of a review but decide against it.
FOUR! Poor fielding! Abbas was maybe tired after bowling a long spell. Full ball on middle, Woakes drives it past the bowler. Abbas chases after it and tumbles but fails to stop it. Four signalled.
EDGY! Good length ball on off, Woakes looks to defend but it takes the edge and goes through the gully region. A couple.
Full ball outside off, Woakes lets it go to the keeper.
FOUR! This is one of the rare deliveries that Afridi has bowled. It is full and wide. Woakes strides forward and drives it through the cover region for a boundary.
Good length ball on middle, Woakes defends it to mid on.
Starts with a full one outside off, Buttler drives it to deep point for a single.
Flatter one on middle, Chris tucks it to mid-wicket.
Short ball around off, Woakes cuts it to point for another dot.
Flat one outside off, Chris punches it to deep cover for a single.
Flatter delivery outside off, Buttler lets it go to the keeper.
Outside off, Buttler pushes it to deep cover for a single.
Good length ball outside off, Buttler leaves it alone.
On a length outside off, Buttler shoulders arms to it.
FOUR! Lovely drive from Buttler! He is looking comfortable now! Full delivery outside off, Buttler drives it through the cover region for a boundary.
Length ball on off, Jos prods forward and blocks it to mid off.
Well played! Full delivery on middle, nipping in. Buttler flicks it to fine leg for a couple.
Outside off, not played at.
Flatter ball outside off, Woakes punches it to deep cover for a single.
Very full ball on off, Buttler pushes it to deep cover for a single.
Floated on middle, Woakes pushes it back to the bowler.
On off, Chris plays it to cover.
Tossed up ball outside off, Woakes leaves it alone.
Quicker ball on off, Woakes defends it out onto the pitch.
NO BALL! Good length ball on middle, Buttler works it to mid-wicket. Afridi has overstepped.
Full ball on off, Buttler drives it to mid off for nothing.
Full ball outside off, Jos shoulders arms to it.
Outside off, Buttler has no problems in leaving it alone.
Good length ball outside off, Jos does not bother playing at that one.
Comes around the wicket and dishes a length ball outside off, Buttler does not fiddle with it as he leaves it alone.
Full ball outside off, Buttler makes another leave to the keeper. LUNCH ON DAY 3.
Starts off with one outside off, it is left alone.
One more delivery outside off, Woakes does not play at it.
Loose! Woakes' patience finally gives in. He gets away with one though. It is another one outside off, wider this time. CW goes after it away from his body but misses.
Cracking shot! Fuller and on off, Woakes just puts bat to ball, it races off the willow but straight to the fielder at covers.
Beauty! Goes wide of the crease, it lands on a length, straightens and then zips through. Woakes is squared up as he tries to defend. Gets beaten.
A maiden to begin with! On a length and outside off, Woakes lets it be.
Flighted ball outside off, Buttler lets it be.

OUT! TIMBER! Right through the gate! Yasir Shah strikes on his second ball after Lunch and it is the big one of Buttler. He walks back without adding any runs after the break and he probably takes England's hopes of getting close to the Pakistan total with him. Lovely delivery. Gives it nice amount of loop and lands it on off, Buttler looks to play for turn, he ends up playing outside the line and also leaves the gap between bat and pad. It sneaks it through as it skidded on and clips the off pole. It was the tiniest gap between bat and pad but it goes through. The visitors will be sensing a big lead now.
Tossed up on off, Bess defends it onto the ground.
One more flighted ball around middle, Bess keeps it out nicely.
On middle, Bess gets right behind the line and keeps it out.
A beauty to end a beautiful over! This is given nice amount of loop and it lands on off, spins away sharply. Bess prods forward to block but is beaten by the away turn.

NOT OUT! Missing leg! Not sure why Pakistan went for the review there. They probably got a little too excited. Naseem Shah too wasn't that interested when he appealed. This is angled into the pads, Woakes looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pads. An appeal more from the players behind the wicket but it is turned down. Pakistan review. Replays show that they lose one.
Goes short, Woakes pulls it nicely but to the man at mid on.
Well fielded! On middle, this is clipped nicely towards the mid on fielder. He dived to his right and ensures it is only a single.
Outside off, Bess does not bother playing at it.
Shorter and on off, Bess stays back and keeps it out.
A bumper to end, it is ducked under.
Slower through the air and on middle, Woakes prods forward and defends it out.
Another tossed up ball on off, CW keeps it out.
Shah is bowling with a lot of control here! He floats it up and lands it on off, Woakes is once again solid in defense.
Quicker and outside off, it is left alone.
Slider, quicker and on middle, Woakes stays back and defends it onto the ground.
On middle, Woakes manages to defend it. Another maiden from Shah.
Angled into the middle pole, Bess pushes it towards mid on for one.
Attacks the stumps again, Woakes gets right behind the line and plays it to mid off.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
On middle, Woakes keeps it out again.
On middle, CW gets right behind the line and defends it.
Just a single from the over! On middle, it is worked towards mid-wicket.
Tossed up delivery on off, Bess pushes it to point.
Flighted delivery outside off, Bess shoulders arms to this one.
Loopy delivery on middle, Bess blocks it off the front foot.

OUT! Edged and that is a superb catch from Shafiq! Another one for Shah, really would love to know what he had for Lunch because he is on fire at the moment. Another rippa of a delivery. Turn, bounce and he gets the breakthrough. It lands on off and then spins away sharply. Bess looks to defend but due to the turn and the extra bounce, it hits the shoulder and lobs to the right of the first slip fielder. He moves there, dives and takes it with two hands. Three for Yasir.
Tossed up delivery on off, Archer guides it towards third man. The fielder chases it and does well to stop it. The batsmen get two runs.
Floated delivery on off, Archer taps it through point for a single.
On the stumps, defended.
Slightly fuller, Archer is rooted to his crease as he defends it.
Angled into the batter, it is worked towards mid-wicket for one.
The batsman has flicked the ball off his pads. They pick up a single.
Good length ball outside off, Archer looks to defend but misses.
BOUNCER! It is bowled around middle, ducked under.
Tossed up delivery on off, Woakes defends it off the front foot.
Full delivery on off, Woakes drives it through mid off for a single.
BEATEN! Floated delivery outside off, Archer looks to defend but misses it.
On middle, Archer flicks it towards the leg side.
Loopy delivery on off, Archer defends it off the front foot.
Full delivery on off, Archer drives it to mid off.

A direct hit and Woakes would have been a goner! A big mix-up. He taps the ball towards covers and then takes off. Archer is not interested in the run. Yasir gets to the ball, picks it up and fires it at the keeper's end but misses it by a whisker. Woakes' dive would not have saved him there.
Full delivery on off, Woakes drives it through covers for a single.
Good length delivery outside off, Archer shoulders arms to this one.
Naseem Shah bowls a yorker on off, Archer looks to dig it out but gets an outside edge. It goes past second slip towards third man. The batsmen pick up a couple.
On a good length on off, Archer defends it off the front foot.
Good length delivery on middle, Archer looks to defend but gets hit on the pads. The bowler appeals for lbw but the umpire shakes his head. Replays show that there was an inside edge on that one.
Floated on off, Woakes pushes it back to the bowler.
Tossed up on middle, Chris defends it out onto the pitch.
Well kept by Rizwan! Looped up ball outside off, turning away. Woakes lets it go to the keeper.

OUT! TIMBER! What a delivery from Yasir Shah! 4th wicket for Yasir. Woakes has to go and England are on the verge of conceding a big lead. Short and quicker on middle, Woakes rocks on his back foot and looks to pull. He misses and the ball goes onto hit the middle stump. Brilliant stuff from the leg spinner. Pakistan are right on top. England are still 156 behind.
Looped up ball on middle, Broad defends it back to the bowler. The third umpire signals it a No Ball.
Floated on middle, Broad defends it back to the bowler.
Tossed up ball on off, Stuart defends it to cover.
Decent fielding! Shorter and outside off, it is cut towards point where the fielder dives to his right and saves at least two. One taken.
Down the leg side, Broad looks to flick but misses.
Where was Broad running there? This is fuller and on middle, it is worked towards mid on. Broad is off but is sent back in time.
FOUR! Angles it into the pads, it is a little too full. Broad works it through square leg and bags a boundary.
EDGY FOUR! Fortunate boundary but England won't mind a few more like this. A yorker on leg pole, Broad looks to jam it out but it goes off the underedge down towards the fine leg fence.
FOUR! Smacked! Bonus runs for England. Three boundaries in a row! This is the best of the lot. Length and outside off, Broad hammers it through covers for a boundary.
Tossed up delivery on off, Archer plays it to point.
Full delivery on off, Archer lofts it over covers. The batsmen take a single.

NOT OUT! But that was lazy running by Archer! This is swept behind square on the leg side. The batters go for one. The fielder fires it to the keeper who whips the bails off and appeals. The umpire takes it upstairs. Archer was casually taking the run but he has made it in the end.
Floated on middle, Archer looks to flick but gets a leading edge on that one. It lands safely towards covers. A single taken.
The batsman shows the full face of the bat and defends the ball off the back foot.
On middle, Broad flicks it to mid-wicket.
Tossed up delivery on off, Archer defends it off the back foot.
Flighted delivery on middle, Archer keeps it out.
FOUR! Good shot! Full delivery on off, Archer drives it through covers for a boundary.
Loopy delivery on middle, Archer keeps it out.
Floated delivery on off, Archer blocks it off the front foot.

NOT OUT! Broad is well in! A low full toss on middle, Broad drives it straight back. Shadab gets a hand on it and the ball goes to hit the stumps and towards mid off. Pakistan put up an appeal for run out and the third umpire is called into question. The replays roll in and they show that Broad had his feet on the ground. A single.
On middle, it is defended.
Outside off, left alone.

NOT OUT! A big gap between bat and ball! Another waste of a review. This though is another excellent delivery. Yasir is giving the ball a lot of rip. It lands on off and then spins away sharply. Archer goes back and tries to defend. It goes past the outside edge. There is an appeal from the keeper, the bowler joins in late. The umpire shakes his head. Babar Azam really likes it and hence, Pakistan review. Replays show that the on-field call is the right one.
The googly on the pads, Archer looks to flick but it hits the pad and goes towards fine leg. Two taken. Leg byes signalled.
Archer eases it down to long on for one.
Defended off the back foot by the batsman.
Loopy on middle, Archer defends it back to the bowler.
Tossed up outside off, Archer pushes it to long off for a single.
Floated on off, Broad pushes it to cover for a single.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! What a ball from Shadab Khan! Archer cannot believe that he has been given out but eventually walks off. Floated ball around off, which spins away. Archer looks to defend but it takes the gloves and goes into the mitts of the keeper. Pakistan put up an appeal and the finger goes up. Archer stands in disbelief but then walks back to the pavilion. England still 129 runs behind.
Loopy ball outside off, Anderson looks to push but fails to get any bat on it.
Tossed up on off, Anderson pushes it to the off side and takes a single. The fielder has a shy at the keeper's end but the batsman is in.
Loopy ball on middle, Anderson works it to short leg.
Tossed up ball on off, Anderson looks to defend but gets hit on the pads.
FOUR! Well played! Flighted on off, Anderson reverse sweeps it to the third man region for a boundary.
Down the leg side, Anderson looks to flick but misses.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
Tosses this one on middle, Anderson flicks it to short leg.
Tossed up delivery on off, Broad drives it through mid off. Khan chases after it and collects. He tumbles, collects and throws it back to the bowler's end but misses it.
Flighted delivery on middle, Broad defends it off the back foot.
Loopy delivery on off, Broad blocks it off the front foot.

NOT OUT! Umpire's call it is. Floated on middle, turning a little, Broad looks to defend but misses and gets rapped on the pads. There is an appeal for LBW but nothing from the umpire. Pakistan take the review. There is nothing on Ultra Edge but the Ball Tracker shows that it is umpire's call on hitting the stumps.
The batsman shows the full face of the bat and defends the ball off the back foot.
Flatter one on middle, Broad flicks it to deep square leg for a single.
SIX! That is huge! Flighted delivery on middle, Broad plays a slog sweep over mid-wicket for a maximum.

DROPPED AND FOUR! Shadab Khan drops a sitter! Knowing how good he is, he should have taken it with his eyes closed! This is tossed up outside off, Broad looks to sweep but it pitches in the rough and there is extra bounce. The top edge is induced. It goes high up in the air towards Shadab Khan who settles under it at deep square leg but spills it. To add salt to the wound, it rolls into the fence behind. Yasir Shah is not happy. 10 from the first two balls.
12 from the first three balls! Handy runs these. On off, it is slapped through covers for two.
On off, kept out.
The batsman shows the full face of the bat and defends the ball off the back foot.
On middle, it is defended nicely.
Flighted delivery on off, Anderson looks to play a reverse sweep but gets hit on the pads.
Full delivery on off, Anderson drives it through mid off. The batsmen get two runs.

OUT! LBW! That's it! England all out and Pakistan lead by 107 runs. Brilliant stuff from Pakistan! Floated on middle, Anderson looks to sweep but misses and gets hit on the pads. Pakistan put up an appeal. The umpire raises his finger. Anderson reviews. The Ultra Edge shows no bat and the Ball Tracker shows that all reds. ENGLAND ALL OUT FOR 219.
Starts off with one outside off, it is left alone.
Beauty! Good use of the angle. It lands on off and then slants away. Masood looks to defend but gets beaten. He does so inside the line.
Masood misses out there! On the pads, it is worked nicely but straight to square leg.
Back of a length and on off, Masood keeps it out.
Well wide outside off, Masood does not fiddle with it.
A maiden to begin with by Anderson! On off, blocked.
Broad starts with a good length ball outside off, Abid lets it go to the keeper.
PAKISTAN ARE UNDERWAY! Full delivery on middle, Pope flicks it to square leg where the fielder dives to make a good stop. A single.
NO BALL! Length ball outside off, Masood leaves it alone. The third umpire signals it a No Ball.
FOUR BYES! Buttler has had a tough time in this Test match! Good length ball outside off, Masood leaves it alone. Buttler fails to collect it and the ball races to the fence.
Length ball on middle, Shan blocks it to mid-wicket.
On a length on off, Masood looks to defend but it takes the outside edge and goes to gully.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Strangled down the leg side! England needed an early wicket and they have got one. Masood scored a century in the first innings but gets out for a duck in the second. How fortunes change! Good length ball on the pads, Masood looks to flick but it goes off the middle of the bat and into the gloves of Buttler. A huge sigh of relief for Buttler.
BEATEN! On a good length and outside off, Abid looks to defend but misses it due to the seam movement on this one.
Length delivery on middle, Abid flicks it through square leg. The batsmen get two runs.
BEATEN! Good length delivery outside off, Abid looks to defend but misses it.
Outside off, Abid leaves it alone.
Full delivery on off, Abid drives it towards mid off.
Good length delivery outside off, Abid offers no shot to this one.
Good length ball on off, angling in. Azhar defends it to mid-wicket.
On a length outside off, Azhar lets it go to the keeper.
Just short! Good length ball on off, Azhar attempts to defend but it takes the outside edge and goes towards the first slip fielder. It bounces short though. Root seems to have hurt himself there.
Full ball on off, it is pushed to cover off the front foot.
Fullish on middle, Azhar flicks it to mid-wicket for another dot.
Outside off, Azhar lets it go to the keeper.
Back of a length ball on middle, Abid tucks it to mid-wicket.
Full delivery on middle, Abid pushes it to mid on off the front foot.
Good length ball outside off, Abid lets it through to the keeper.
BEATEN! Excellent bowling from Anderson! Good length ball outside off, Abid looks to put bat on ball but fails to make any connection.
Fullish on off, Abid pushes it to mid off.
Outside off, left alone.
Full delivery on off, Azhar pushes it to point.
BEATEN! Brilliant stuff! Good length delivery outside off, Azhar looks to defend but misses it due to the out-swing on this one.
BEATEN! On a good length and outside off, Azhar looks to defend but misses it.
Good length delivery on off, Azhar defends it off the back foot.
Outside off, Azhar offers no shot to this one.
Good length delivery outside off, Azhar shoulders arms to this one.
EDGY FOUR! It went at a catchable height but right through the gap! Good length ball outside off, Abid looks to push but it takes the outside edge and goes through the gully region for a boundary.
Good length ball outside off, Abid leaves it alone.
Abid defends this length ball on off towards point for a dot.

DROPPED! Stokes dropped some catches in the series against West Indies and has put down another one in this Test. Disappointment is written all over his face. England need to take catches like these if they want to make a comeback. This was Root's catch though. Don't understand why Stokes went for it. Good length ball on off, Abid looks to defend but it takes the outside edge and goes towards Root at first slip. Stokes at second slip has different ideas. He moves to his left and tries to take the catch but spills it. It would have been a simple catch for Root. Poor fielding. How costly will this be?
Outside off, left alone.
FOUR! That's adding insult to injury! Anderson is furious as he kicks the ground in anger! Good length ball outside off, Abid drives it through the cover region for a boundary.
On a good length and outside off, Azhar shoulders arms to this one.
BEATEN! Full delivery outside off, Azhar looks to drive but misses it.
Good length delivery on off, Azhar defends it to point.
On a length on middle, Azhar flicks it towards the leg side.
Good length delivery on off, Azhar defends it off the back foot.
Outside off, Azhar offers no shot to this one.
FOUR! Beautifully played from Abid! Good length ball outside off, Abid punches it through the cover region for a boundary. This will frustrate Anderson more.
On a length on off, Abid pushes it to cover.
BEATEN! This is brilliant! Full delivery outside off, Abid looks to push but fails to get any bat on it.
On middle, Abid pushes it to mid on.
Fullish delivery on middle, Abid plays it back to the bowler.
Good length ball on off, Abid blocks it to cover off the front foot. TEA ON DAY 3.
Good length ball on off, Azhar blocks it to point off the front foot.
FOUR! Azhar Ali is off the pair with a classic shot! He will breathe a huge sigh of relief! Full ball on off, Azhar drives it through mid off for a boundary.
FOUR! Poor start from Broad! He is giving freebies to Azhar Ali at the moment! He overpitches this outside off, Azhar lunges forward and creams the drive through the cover region for a boundary.
Length ball on off, Azhar blocks it to cover.
Fullish ball on off, Azhar solidly blocks it to point.
A dot to finish! Good length ball on off, AA defends it to the off side. Good start from Pakistan. 8 from the over.
Archer starts with a full ball on middle, Abid lunges forward and defends it to mid on.
Strays down the leg side! Good length ball down the leg side, Abid looks to flick. Buttler dives to his left and collects it.
Good length ball outside off, Abid shoulders arms to it.
Back of a length ball outside off, Abid hops and punches it to deep point for a single.
Good length ball outside off, Azhar decides to leave it alone.
Fuller one on off, Azhar pushes it to mid off.
On a length on middle, Abid pushes it to mid on.
Some confusion but safe in the end! Good length ball on middle, Abid defends it towards mid off. They think of a single but decide against it.
Good length ball on off, Abid prods forward and defends it to the off side.
Poor fielding! England have been sloppy in the field in this match so far! Full delivery on off, Abid pushes it to mid off where Anderson lets the ball go past him. Two taken.
On a length on middle, Abid blocks it back to the bowler.
Good length ball on middle, Abid works it to mid-wicket for a single.
Full ball outside off, Abid shoulders arms to it.
Back of a length ball on off, Abid punches it to the cover region.
Here comes the short one! It is bowled around middle, Abid ducks under it.
Slightly short outside off, Abid pushes it to deep cover for a run.
Good length ball outside off, Azhar lets it go to the keeper.
Outside off, not played at.
Flatter one on middle, Abid defends out onto the pitch.
Floated ball on off, Abid pushes it to cover.
Loopy ball on middle, Abid blocks it back to the bowler.
Tossed up on off, Abid prods forward and blocks it to cover.
That landed on the rough! Floated on off, it hits the rough and spins in. Abid looks to defend but hits the gloves and lobs towards short leg. It lands safely though.

OUT! CAUGHT! This is really poor batting! There was absolutely no need of hitting this shot! Why attempt it when there is a fielder present in the deep? This is the exact reason that Bess was brought into the attack. Bess tosses this one on middle, Abid goes on his knees and then looks to sweep but the ball bounces a little extra and it goes off the top edge towards deep mid-wicket. Chris Woakes comes ahead and takes a simple catch. Pakistan are effectively 140 for 2.
Archer bowls a bouncer, Azhar does well to duck under it.
NO BALL! Archer oversteps! FOUR! Full delivery on off, Azhar looks to defend but gets an outside edge. It goes between first slip and second slip towards third man for a boundary.
Good length delivery on off, Azhar blocks it off the back foot.
Full delivery on off, Azhar drives it back towards the bowler.
On a good length on off, Azhar keeps it out.
Length delivery on off, Azhar punches it towards the off side.
Archer bowls a yorker on middle, Azhar does well to dig it out.
Floated on middle, Babar plays it back to the bowler.
On middle, Azam defends it back to the bowler.
Flatter one on the middle stump line, Azam blocks it solidly back to Bess.
Tossed up on off, Babar pushes it to point.
Loops this one on middle, Azam defends it out onto the pitch.
Shorter on middle, Azam works it to deep square leg for a single.
Very full ball on off, Babar digs it out to cover.
Good length ball outside off, Azam shoulders arms to it.
Fullish on off, BA pushes it to mid off.
Back of a length ball on off, Azam defends it to point. He wants the single but is sent back.
Well fielded! Good length ball around off, Azam guides it towards gully. Burns dives and makes a good stop. Saved few runs for his side.
A couple! Good length ball outside off, Babar punches it to deep point and picks up a couple.
Loopy ball on middle, Azhar flicks it to mid-wicket.
On off, Ali strides forward and blocks it to cover.
Flatter ball on middle, Ali tucks it to deep mid-wicket for a single.
Bess tosses this on middle, Babar blocks it back to the bowler.
Flatter one outside off, spins in after pitching! Azam carefully lets it go to the keeper.
Gets away with a full toss! Bess bowls one around off, Azam misses out as he punches it straight to point.
Good length ball on middle, Azhar defends it out onto the pitch.
Full ball on middle, Ali drives it through mid on and picks up a couple before the fielder cuts it off.
On a length on middle, Ali whips it through mid-wicket and picks up another couple of runs.
Back of a length ball on middle, Azhar works it to mid-wicket.
BOUNCER! Ali almost falls onto his stumps! It is bowled around middle, Azhar ducks under it but falls in the process. Luckily, not onto the stumps.
Outside off, not played at.
Good length ball on off, Azam blocks it to cover.
Full ball on off, Babar pushes it through extra cover and collects a couple. Good batting.
Good length delivery, angling in from outside off, Babar shoulders arms to it.
Good length ball on off, Babar blocks it to cover and shouts a loud no to his partner.

OUT! CAUGHT! Stokes does not drop this one! Azam falters this time. Woakes comes into the attack and strikes immediately. Brilliant from Woakes and England are making a comeback in this match. Chris dishes a good length ball around off, Azam looks to defend but it takes the outside edge and goes towards second slip. Stokes dives to his left and takes a good catch. Pakistan lead by 155.
Fullish on middle, Azam flicks it to mid-wicket.
Tossed up delivery on middle, Ali looks to flick but gets it off the pads. It goes towards fine leg. The batsmen take a single. The umpire gives it as a leg bye.
BEATEN! Flighted delivery just outside off, Shafiq looks to defend but misses it due to the turn on this one.
Floated delivery on middle, Shafiq blocks it off the back foot.
Full delivery on off, Asad drives it to mid off.
On middle, Shafiq defends it out.
Flighted delivery on middle, Shafiq flicks it towards fine leg. The batsmen get two runs.
Good length ball on off, Azhar blocks it to the off side.
Full ball on the pads, Ali whips it to fine leg for a single.
FOUR! Not the right line! Easy pickings for Asad Shafiq! Full ball on the pads, Shafiq flicks it to deep square leg. The fielder runs across and dives but the ball touches the ropes.
Back of a length on the pads, Asad tucks it to deep square leg for a single.
BEATEN! That is some bowling from Woakes! Good length ball around off, moving away. Ali looks to defend but misses. The keeper and Root are interested but Woakes says no.
On a length on middle and leg, Ali looks to flick but misses and gets hit on the pads. An appeal is made for LBW but nothing from the umpire.

Tossed up delivery on middle, Shafiq drives it towards mid on and takes a single. The fielder goes for a direct hit at the keeper's end but misses it. It goes as overthrows and the batsmen take an extra run.
Flighted delivery on off, Shafiq blocks it off the front foot.
On middle, Asad defends it off the back foot.

Turn and bounce on this one! Floated delivery on off, Shafiq looks to defend but gets hit on the glove.

OUT! LBW! That looked plumb! The reverse swing does the trick for Woakes! He bowls on a different level when it comes to bowling in England. The home side are not out of it yet. Brilliant stuff from Chris. Full delivery on middle, it reverses after pitching. Ali looks to flick but misses and gets rapped on the pads. England appeal and the umpire raises the dreaded finger. Azhar discusses with Shafiq for the review but decides against it. Good decision as the Ball Tracker shows all reds. Would have been a waste of a review. Pakistan lead by 170 runs.
On a length on off, Rizwan defends it to cover. End of a very good over from Woakes.
Loopy ball on off, Asad defends it back to the bowler.
Short ball on middle, Shafiq pulls it to deep square leg for a single.
On the pads, Mohammad pushes it to mid on.

Full delivery on off, Rizwan pushes it to mid off.
Flatter one on middle, Mohammad plays it back to Bess off the back foot.

Was that a drop? Yes it was! Another dropped catch from England! It was a tough one as it was travelling quickly but it should have been taken. Back of a  length ball outside off, Shafiq cuts it to the point region where Anderson dives and gets a hand on it but fails to hold on. Two taken before the fielder cuts it off.
Down the leg side, Shafiq looks to flick but misses.
Full on middle, Shafiq defends it to mid off.
On a length on off, Shafiq blocks it back to the bowler.
Fullish on off, Shafiq looks to defend but it goes off the outside edge towards gully.
Good length ball on off, Asad blocks it to cover.
Flatter one on off, Rizwan pushes it to cover and takes a single. Mohammad is off the mark.
Tossed up on middle, Shafiq flicks it to mid-wicket.

Back of a length ball on middle, Rizwan tucks it to square leg.
Short ball outside off, Mohammad punches it to cover off the back foot.
Well played! Fullish ball on middle, Rizwan flicks it wide of mid on. Archer dives and stops it. Keeps it down to a single.
An appeal for LBW turned down! Good length ball around off, angling in. Rizwan looks to defend but misses and gets hit on the pads. There is a mild appeal for LBW but nothing from the umpire.

Good length ball on middle and leg, Rizwan looks to flick but gets hit on the pads. England appeal but the umpire is not interested. Root seems interested for the review but the others are not. The Ball Tracker rolls in and it shows that it is missing the stumps.
The batsman works it down the leg side.
FOUR! Positive cricket from Rizwan! Nice way to get his first boundary of the innings! Full toss on middle, Rizwan sweeps it to the deep square leg region for a boundary.
Flatter on off, Rizwan punches it to cover.
Floated on middle, Rizwan defends it back to the bowler.

Misfield! Shorter outside off, Rizwan punches it to point. It is uppish for a while. Broad comes ahead in order to take the catch but it bounces in front and spins away from him. The ball rolls to deep point and the batters take three.
Floated on middle, Shafiq blocks it out.
Flighted ball on middle, Shafiq comes down the track and looks to heave it away. It goes off the inner half of the bat towards the leg side.

Flighted delivery on middle, Rizwan blocks it off the front foot.
Loopy delivery on middle, Rizwan makes room and punches it through point. The batsmen get two runs.
Short delivery on off, Rizwan plays a late cut towards third man. The fielder chases it and does well to stop it just before the ropes. The batsmen get three runs.

Good length ball on middle, Rizwan flicks it to deep square leg for a single.

Cracking delivery from Anderson! But has Buttler dropped another one? No as per the replays! Buttler will be relieved! This was a peach of a delivery. Good length ball around off, Rizwan looks to defend but he seems to have missed. England go up in appeal but they see that Buttler has not collected it. The Ultra Edge shows that there is no bat on it.
FOUR! Good shot! Flighted delivery on middle, Shafiq plays a paddle sweep towards fine leg for a boundary. The lead is now 200.
Floated delivery on middle, Shafiq keeps it out.
Tossed up delivery on off, Asad defends it off the front foot.

On off, Shafiq blocks it off the back foot.
Floated delivery on middle, Shafiq defends it out.
FOUR! That's a cracking shot from Mohammad Rizwan! He is looking really good out there! Good length ball on off, Rizwan drives it through mid off and collects a boundary.
On a length on middle, Mohammad defends it back to the bowler.
Short ball on middle, Rizwan pulls it to deep square leg for a single.
Good length ball on middle, Shafiq flicks it to fine leg for a single.

OUT! RUN OUT! Excellent piece of fielding has resulted in a wicket. This partnership was building and England have picked up a wicket at the right time. Shafiq walks back disappointed. Good length ball on off, Rizwan defends it to cover and takes off for a single. He is hesitant but then they decide to go for it. Sibley comes across, picks it up with one hand and has a shy at the stumps. He hits and the third umpire is called into question. From the looks of Shafiq, he thinks he is a goner. The replays roll in and they show that Shafiq is well out.  Excellent stuff from Dom Sibley.
Defended off the back foot by the batsman.
Short delivery on middle, Rizwan pulls it through mid-wicket for a run.
Flighted delivery on middle, Shadab defends it off the back foot.
Loopy delivery on off, Khan keeps it out.
FOUR! That is put away! Short delivery on middle, Khan pulls it through mid-wicket for a boundary.
Floated delivery on off, Shadab defends it off the back foot.
Short delivery on off, Shadab cuts it to point.
Full delivery on middle, Rizwan flicks it through mid-wicket. The batsmen pick up a couple.
On a length on off, Rizwan taps it to covers.
Full delivery on middle, Rizwan flicks it through square leg for a single.
Length delivery on off, Khan guides it towards third man. The fielder chases it and does well to stop it. The batsmen get two runs.
BEATEN! On a good length and outside off, Shadab looks to defend but misses it.
NO BALL! Anderson oversteps and the third umpire calls it a No Ball. Full delivery on middle, Khan flicks it to mid-wicket.
EDGY FOUR! Luck is favouring Pakistan! On a length on off, Shadab looks to defend but it takes the edge and goes through the gully region for a boundary.
Stokes starts with a short one outside off, Rizwan looks to cut but it takes the inside edge and goes to the keeper who collects it on the bounce.
Short ball on middle, Rizwan pulls it to fine leg for a single.
PLAY AND A MISS! Looks like Shadab wants to take Stokes on! Shortish outside off, Khan looks to pull but fails to get any bat on it.
BEATEN! Good length ball around off, Khan looks to defend but fails to get any bat on it.

OUT! LBW! Umpire's call it is! Ben Stokes does it again! We have seen it many times that whenever England need a wicket, Ben Stokes provides them with one. Lovely bowling from Ben Stokes. Good length ball on off, angling in. Rizwan looks to flick but misses and gets hit on the pads. England appeal and the umpire raises the finger. Rizwan opts for the review. There is nothing on Ultra Edge and the Ball Tracker shows that it is umpire's call on hitting the stumps. Rizwan has to go. Pakistan lead by 227.
Good length ball outside off, Yasir leaves it alone.
BEATEN! Excellent stuff! Good length delivery outside off, Yasir looks to defend but fails to get any bat on it.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.

Good length ball on middle, played back to the bowler.

OUT! LBW! All reds and Khan has to go. England are right back in this game! Brilliant bowling from Broad. He bowled shorter before this and now dishes a full delivery on middle. Shadab hangs back in his crease, expecting another bouncer. He looks to flick but gets rapped on the pads. Broad and the rest put up a huge appeal but nothing from the umpire. Root takes the review. The Ultra Edge shows no spike. What about Ball Tracker? It shows all reds. Shadab has to go now. Pakistan lead by 229.
Full delivery outside off, Shah drives it through covers. The fielder chases it and does well to stop it. The batsmen get two runs.
FOUR! Nicely played! On a length on middle, Shah flicks it towards fine leg for a boundary.
NO BALL! The third umpire calls No Ball as Stokes oversteps! Short delivery on leg, Yasir nudges it towards square leg. The batsmen cross ends.
Good length delivery outside off, Afridi leaves it alone.

BEATEN! Excellent delivery! Good length ball outside off, Afridi looks to defend but fails to get any bat on it.

The batsman has nudged the ball fine down the leg side.

OUT! CAUGHT! What a nasty delivery from Stokes! You cannot keep him out of the game! He failed with the bat but he is delivering big time with the ball! Short ball around middle, Afridi looks to fend it away but gets a glove on it and it lobs towards gully. Burns comes ahead and takes the simplest of catches. Pakistan are effectively 244 for 8.
Good length ball down the leg side, Abbas lets it go to the keeper.
Outside off, not played at.
Full ball on middle, Abbas pushes it to mid on. STUMPS ON DAY 3.
Pakistan are underway immediately! Archer starts with a good length ball on middle, Yasir flicks it to deep mid-wicket for an easy couple.
FOUR! Very well played! The lead moves to 250 in some style! Short ball around middle, Yasir pulls it to deep mid-wicket for a boundary.
FOUR! Wow, what a start for Pakistan! 10 already off the first three balls! Short ball around middle, Yasir upper cuts it over the keeper's head for another boundary.
On a length on middle, Yasir works it to deep square leg for a single.
Full ball on middle, Abbas flicks it to mid-wicket.
Good length ball on middle, Abbas solidly blocks it back to the bowler. Good start for Pakistan. 11 runs from the over. The lead moves up to 255.

FOUR! Yasir is playing a gem of a knock here! Valuable, valuable runs so far. He has raced to 27 off just 20 balls! Good length ball on off, Yasir heaves it to the deep mid-wicket region for a boundary.

Goes for another big shot but does not time it well! Length ball on off, Yasir looks to hammer it over mid off but does not time it well. Luckily for him, it lands safely in front of the mid off fielder.
SIX! That's a big shot alright! The players in the dressing room are standing in applaud for this knock! Good length ball on middle, Shah lifts it over the deep mid-wicket region for a maximum.
Good length ball on off, Shah blocks it to cover off the front foot.

OUT! EDGED AND TAKEN! With the field coming in, Yasir Shah thought that he could have gone for a big one but fails as he nicks one to the keeper. End of a wonderful little cameo from Shah! He has added some valuable runs to the lead. Broad dishes a good length ball outside off, Shah clears his front leg and looks to go over mid off but the ball takes the outside edge and goes to Buttler who makes no mistake this time. Pakistan lead by 265 runs.
FOUR! Smashed! Naseem too is looking to play his shots! Despite a wicket, it is a terrific over for Pakistan! Full on middle, Naseem thrashes it over the bowler's head and into the fence.
Over the mid off fielder! Good length ball around off, Abbas looks to go over mid off but does not time it so well. It goes over the fielder and the batters pick up a couple.
Fullish on middle, Naseem flicks it to mid-wicket for a single.
FOUR LEG BYES! Pakistan will take the runs anyhow they come! Short ball around middle, Naseem looks to pull but it takes the shoulder and goes over the keeper for a boundary.

OUT! TIMBER! That's the end of that! Pakistan end with a lead of 276. 32 runs were added today and 277 is not an easy target to chase! Good length ball on middle, Naseem looks to swing it away but misses and the ball goes onto hit the stumps. PAKISTAN ALL OUT FOR 169.

Nicely driven! Afridi overpitches it outside off, Burns takes a stride forward and drives it through cover for a couple.
NO BALL! Good length ball on off, Burns defends it to cover. The third umpire signals it a No ball.
Pacy delivery! Good length ball outside off, Burns shoulders arms to it.
FOUR! Poor bowling from Afridi! Not the line to bowl! Good length ball on the pads, Burns flicks it to the fine leg region for a boundary.
Length ball on middle, Burns blocks it back to the bowler.

Extra bounce! Good length ball on middle, bouncing a little extra. Sibley looks to flick but it takes the leading edge and goes towards the cover region.
BEATEN! Lovely stuff from Abbas! Just lovely! Good length ball outside off, moving away, Sibley looks to defend but misses it completely.
Back of a length on middle, Dom works it to mid-wicket.
A bumper! It is on the body of the batter, Burns keeps it out.

Full delivery on off, Sibley blocks it to cover.
On a length on off, Sibley plays it to gully off the front foot.

Fullish ball on off, Burns solidly blocks it to point. A maiden over.
Afridi dishes a good length ball outside off, Sibley lets it go to the keeper.
Full ball on middle, Sibley drives it straight to mid on for a dot.
Good length delivery outside the off stump line, Sibley shoulders arms to it.
Short ball around off, Sibley sways away from it.

Finds the gap! Fullish ball outside off, Sibley drives it through extra cover. The fielder chases it down but cannot stop the batters from taking three.
Full ball on middle, Sibley pushes it to mid on.
EDGY FOUR! Lucky but Sibley won't mind as long as the runs keep coming! Good length ball on off, Sibley looks to defend but it goes off the outside edge and through the gully region for a boundary.
On a length on middle, Sibley tucks it to mid-wicket.
A single now! Good length ball on middle, Sibley works it to mid-wicket for a single.
Good length ball outside off, Burns leaves it alone.

Naseem starts with a good length ball outside off, at 136 kph. Sibley has no problems in leaving it alone.
Outside off, not played at.
Good length ball outside off, Sibley shoulders arms to it.

Good length ball outside off, Dom leaves it alone.
That's a pacy delivery! Good length ball outside off, Sibley shoulders arms. It wobbles a bit after pitching and Rizwan fails to collect it cleanly.

OUT! LBW! Coming around the wicket does the trick for Abbas! Abbas was confident in his appeal! Brilliant piece of bowling from Abbas! He has delivered for Pakistan yet again. Good length ball on off, angling in. Burns looks to defend but misses and gets rapped on the pads. Abbas appeals and the umpire raises his finger. Burns has a discussion with Sibley and goes for the review. The Ultra Edge rolls in and it shows no bat. What about Ball Tracker? It shows that it is umpire's call. Review retained. Burns walks off but not before engaging in some words with the Pakistan players. England still need 255 runs.
Root is off the mark! Full delivery on middle, Root flicks it towards mid on and collects a single.
Outside off, left alone.

Good length ball outside off, Sibley lets it go to the keeper.
Good length ball on middle, Sibley works it to mid-wicket.
Another beauty! He goes wide of the crease and angles it into the off pole. It lands on a length and then straightens. Root looks to play the original trajectory but gets beaten.
One more delivery on a length and around middle, Root keeps it out.
Outside off, left alone.
Shorter and around off, Root stands tall and pushes it to point.
FOUR! Easy-peasy! Slips one onto the pads, Root is way too strong there, he works it through square leg and bags a boundary.
Shorter and on off, Root goes back and keeps it out. So just the boundary from the over. Overall a good one by Shah.
A full toss on the pads, it is worked towards mid-wicket for one.
Slightly shorter and around off, it turns away. Root has enough time to go back, adjust to the turn and push it through covers for one.
Gives it nice amonut of flight. It is a fraction fuller than it needs to be. Easily blocked.
Once again a little too full, on middle, Sibley works it through square leg for a run.
BEATEN! Almost a replay of how Root got out in the first innings! Poor shot. This is a little too close to cut. Shortish and outside off, it skids through. Root goes back and looks to cut but misses.
Does the right thing this time, Yasir invites Root to cut again by bowling a slider outside off. Root resists and lets it be.
Fuller and on middle, it is pushed to mid on.

WOW! What a delivery! Pace, carry, movement, it had everything but does not produce a wicket. It is angled into the off pole again from wide of the crease. It pitches, straightens and also takes off. Beats the outside edge of Sibley's bat as he tries to defend.
On middle, Sibley gets right behind the line and defends it.
Another back of a length ball, Sibley keeps it out again.
A bumper now! Ducked under. Mixing it up nicely is Shah.
A maiden! A good one from Shah! On off, blocked.

It goes off the outside edge but lands just short of first slip. The slip fielders are probably standing a yard behind for Shah. He is more of a skiddy bowler so you would want to be a couple of steps ahead than you usually are for another bowler.
An appeal but turned down. Angled into the pads, Sibley looks to flick but gets an inside edge onto the pads.

On middle, worked to short leg.

PLAY AND A MISS! Flatter one outside off, Sibley looks to cut but fails to get any bat on it.
