Back of a length and on off, Root guides it towards point.
Good length and on middle, kept out.
Shorter and outside off, Root goes back and cuts but to point. Batting seems to have gotten a touch easier at the moment.
FOUR! Sibley moves into the 30s! Flighted delivery outside off, it turns away a touch. Sibley opens the face of the bat, plays it with the turn and it goes behind point for a boundary.
Outside off, it is left alone.
Another leg spinner on off, Sibley defends it out.
Tossed up outside off, Sibley watches it go to the keeper.
Floats it up on off, DS keeps it out with ease.
Fuller and on off, Sibley drives it towards covers.

Leading edge but safe! Luck not going Pakistan's way at the moment. There are two gullies in place but it evades both. It is on middle, it straightens a touch. Root looks to work it on the leg side which is against the movement. It goes off the leading edge but short of point.
Angled into the pads, Root misses the flick and wears it onto the pads.
The batsman lets the ball go outside his off stump.
On the off stump, defended out nicely.
On middle, kept out.
Angled into the off pole, Root stays behind and defends it onto the ground.
Floats it up on off, Sibley defends it nicely.
Yasir goes around the wicket. He lands it outside leg. Sibley pads it away.
Once again this lands outside the leg pole. Sibley is happy to offer no shot.
Another one which is bowled outside leg. Sibley is happy to kick it away.
Fires this on middle, DS keeps it out.
The last ball is also padded away as it lands outside the leg pole.
On middle, defended.
Angled into the pads, it is worked towards mid-wicket.
Well played! A length ball on middle, it takes a chunk out of the surface when it lands. Takes off after pitching. Root does well to defend it by taking one hand off the handle.
Root now takes a few steps ahead and defends this ball on off.
Outside off, not played at.
Back of a length and on off, Root stays back and keeps it out.
Flatter on middle, Sibley defends it out.
On the pads, Sibley blocks it out to the leg side.
Floated on middle, padded away.
Another tossed up ball on the leg stump line, Sibley pads it away.
The batsman offers no stroke and gets hit on the pad.

Full ball on middle, Sibley flicks it to deep square leg and picks up a couple. 50-run partnership comes up between the two. An important one for England. They would know that their job is only half done and they need to continue.
Back of a length and on off, defended.
Good shot for no runs! Slightly shorter and just outside off, Root stays leg side of the ball and guides it to gully.
Angled into the off pole, Root blocks it nicely.
Outside off, Root shoulders arms to this one.
Edged but well short! Played that with soft hands did Root! Length and on off, Root looks to defend but it goes off the outside edge well short of the first slip fielder.
A solid defense to end! On off, kept out.
This lands on off and then turns away. Left alone.
This one pitches outside leg and hence, Sibley does not offer a shot.
One more ball outside off, not played at.
Floats it up but lands it outside leg. Padded away.
On middle, it is worked towards mid-wicket.
A couple to end! On middle, it is worked through mid-wicket for two.
Good length ball on off, Root prods forward and pushes it to cover.
TWO LEG BYES! Full ball on the pads, Root looks to flick but misses and gets hit on the pads. The ball goes to deep square leg and the batters pick up a couple of leg byes.
FOUR! Nicely played from Root! He is looking good! Back of a length ball outside off, Root guides it through the gully region for a boundary. England need below 200 now.
On a length on off, Root blocks it to the cover region.
Full delivery on the middle stump line, Root tucks it to deep square leg for a single.
Full delivery on middle, Sibley nudges it to mid-wicket.
FOUR! Excellently cut away by Root! Flatter delivery outside off, Root cuts it through the point region for a boundary.
That bounced a little extra! Shah tosses this one on middle, turns away and bounces. Root does well to leave it alone.
The batsman offers no stroke and is wrapped on the pads.
Full on middle, Root defends it out onto the pitch.
Low full toss on middle, Root sweeps it to deep square leg for a single.

OUT! CAUGHT! Sibley cannot resist the drive and it has cost him! Big wicket for Pakistan and the door has been opened for them. Yasir bowls a floated ball outside off, Sibley's eyes lit up and looks to drive but it takes the outside edge and goes to first slip where Asad Shafiq takes a simple catch. England still need 191 more runs to win.
Good length ball on middle, Root flicks it to mid-wicket for a single.
Back of a length ball on off, Stokes blocks it to mid off.
Fullish ball on off, Stokes taps it to point.

EDGY FOUR! Stokes is off the mark in a tricky fashion! Good length ball on off, Stokes looks to leave it at first but then decides to defend. It goes off the outside edge and through the slip cordon for another boundary.
Outside off, left alone.
Good length ball on middle, Stokes defends it back to the bowler.
FOUR! Lovely controlled shot from Root! Floated on middle, Root reverse sweeps it towards the third man region for a boundary. Moves into the 40s.
On the pads, Root pads it away.
Short delivery outside off, Root punches it to deep cover for a single.
Flatter one on the pads, Stokes pads it away.
Floated on middle, Ben works it to short leg.
Tossed up on middle, Stokes lunges and defends it out.
Full ball on middle, Root pushes it to mid on.
Good length ball on off, Root strides forward and blocks it to cover.
Good length ball on middle, Root defends it back to the bowler.

OUT! CAUGHT! The England skipper is out of here! Big wicket for Pakistan! They will believe that they can win this from here! Brilliant stuff from Naseem Shah. Pakistan are on top now. Good length ball outside off, moving away. Root looks to defend but it takes the outside edge and goes to first slip at a catchable height. Azam will not drop those and Root has to walk back. He got off to a start but like many times in his career, he has thrown it away. England still a long way away from achieving a victory.
Full ball on off, Pope drives it to mid off for nothing.
FOUR! Strays on the pads and it has been punished! 100 up for England! Good length ball on the pads, Pope flicks it to the deep square leg region for a boundary. Pope is also off the mark.
Flatter one on middle, Stokes blocks it back to the bowler.

An appeal for LBW turned down! It has gone off the bat anyway! Loopy ball on off, Stokes looks to flick but it takes the outside edge and rolls to the point region. Yasir appeals but nothing from the umpire.
FOUR! Stokes looks to attack the spinner now! Flighted on middle, Stokes reverse sweeps it through point for a boundary.
Tossed up on middle, Ben flicks it to deep square leg for a single.
Flighted on off, Pope blocks it to point.
Short and outside off, Pope cuts but straight to the point fielder.
Good length ball on middle, Stokes blocks it to mid-wicket.
Very full delivery on off, Stokes digs it out towards point.
Fuller one on middle, Ben whips it but finds the mid-wicket fielder.
Good length ball on middle, Stokes lunges forward and blocks it to the leg side.

NOT OUT! Poor, poor review! It looked like it will go down the leg side from the naked eye. Good length ball on the pads, Stokes comes ahead and looks to flick but misses and gets hit on the pads. Pakistan put up an appeal but nothing from the umpire. Azhar Ali reviews. The Ultra Edge shows nothing while the Ball Tracker shows that it is missing the leg stump. Wonder what made the Pakistan skipper go for the review. A review wasted.
Short ball around middle, Stokes looks to pull but misses.
That turns and stays low! Slow spin though! It lands on middle and turns away, it also stays low. Pope does well to get his bat down in time and keeps it out.
Shorter and outside off, Pope looks to cut but mistimes it towards point.
The slider on middle, Pope goes back and defends it onto the ground.
Close! Pope comes down the track and does not get to the pitch of the ball. He looks to drive but the ball spins away a touch. It goes off the outer half towards cover for one.

That has turned a long way! It lands outside off, it turns back in a long way. Hits Stokes on the pad as he tries to flick. This is going to be a real test for Stokes with the ball turning out off the rough. A huge appeal but the umpire does not agree. Pakistan review after a discussion. Replays show that the on-field call has to be overturned.

OUT! There is a spike on Ultra Edge and Stokes is a goner! He walks off with a shocked look on his face but judging by the replays, it did seem like it kissed the glove. Pakistan are ecstatic as they have got Stokes once again for a low score. Huge wicket as Stokes is a match-winner, the visitors are clear favourites now. Stokes was always going to have a tough time against Yasir with all the rough outside the off stump and he falls to one which lands in it. It takes off and also zips through. Stokes looks to move out of the way but it seems to have taken his glove and Rizwan initially does not take it as it pops out but he hangs on in the second attempt.
Good length ball outside off, Pope leaves it alone.
Fullish ball outside off, Pope pushes it to cover where the fielder makes a half stop. A single taken.
Outside off, left alone.
The sucker ball, full and outside off, Buttler shoulders arms to this one.
Another one outside off, not played at.

That appeal, that celebration but no review! Strange! Afridi was not even bothered about the decision that is how confident he seemed. This lands outside off, Afridi comes from around the wicket. It jags back in sharply. Cuts Buttler into half. It hits the top of the pad and goes to the keeper. Afridi starts celebrating as he appeals but the umpire shakes his head. No review taken.
Flatter one outside off, Pope punches it to cover.
On the pads, Pope flicks it to fine leg for a single.
FOUR! Creamed! Nice way to get off the mark! Floated outside off, Buttler drives it through the extra cover region for a boundary.
Loopy on middle, Jos blocks it to mid on
FOUR! Another super shot from Buttler! Flighted outside off, Buttler hammers it through extra cover. The fielder chases after it and dives but fails to stop it as the ball touches the fence.
Loopy ball on off, Buttler defends it to gully.
Shorter and on off, Pope stays back and keeps it out.
Outside off, left alone.
Shorter and around off, this is defended nicely.
The batsman has pushed it to the cover region. No ball signalled by the Umpire.
Shorter and outside off, it is pushed towards covers.

OUT! In the air... taken! Another one bites the dust! Pope, the hero for England in the first innings is gone for a single-digit score. He though has got a nasty delivery. There is nothing he could have done with that. Just nothing. This lands on off, it is a length ball. Once again it takes off after landing. Pope is caught by surprise. He looks to fend it somehow but the ball hits the glove and lobs towards the off side. Shadab Khan from gully takes a dolly. Half the side back in the hut for England. Everything is falling away pretty quickly here for them. The chase now seems an uphill task from here.
The ball is way outside the off stump, easy leave for the batsman.
A couple! Floated on off, Buttler pushes it to deep cover and picks up a couple.
FOUR! Nicely played! Buttler will look to counterattack! Floated on middle, Buttler reverse sweeps it towards the deep point region for a boundary.
Outside off, left alone.
Floated on the pads, Buttler pads it away.
Short on off, Jos pushes it to mid off.
Full on off, Buttler drives it to long off for a single.
Outside off, it is not played at.
Outside off, it is left alone.
Shorter and around off, Buttler stands tall and defends it.
FOUR! That is played nice and late! Shorter and outside off, Woakes waits for it and then guides it down to third man for a boundary.
Three now! A shorter one and on middle, Woakes looks to pull but does not time it properly. It goes over mid-wicket for three.
Back of a length and on off, Buttler guides it towards point for a run.
Low full toss on the pads, Buttler sweeps it to deep square leg and picks up a couple.
FOUR! That is Jos Buttler at his best! Loopy ball on middle, Buttler sweeps it through square leg for a boundary.
Flighted on the pads, Buttler pads it away.
Top edge but safe! Buttler has to be careful! Loopy ball on middle, Buttler looks to sweep but it takes the top edge. Luckily, it lands safely towards square leg. A single taken.
On middle, Woakes defends it back to the bowler.
Flighted outside off, Woakes leaves it alone.
Shorter and around off, this is pushed through covers for one.
Back of a length and on middle, it is defended nicely.
Shorter in length again and outside off, it is guided through backward point for two.
FOUR! Woakes has been positive right from the word go! Runs flowing now. This is full and outside off, Woakes creams it through covers and it races away to the fence.
Outside off, Woakes guides it towards gully. Once again a shot where he is looking to score.
On middle, defended nicely.
Loopy ball on the pads, Buttler sweeps it but straight to short fine leg.
Flatter on the pads, Buttler works it to the leg side for a single.
FOUR! This shot is so pleasing to the eye! 150 up for England! This partnership is racing! Loopy ball outside off, Woakes lunges forward and drives it through the extra cover region for a boundary.
Shorter on off, Woakes defends it to point for a single.
Floated on the pads, Buttler looks to sweep but it takes the under edge and it goes to short fine leg.
On the pads, Buttler pads it away.
Full delivery on middle, Woakes blocks it back to the bowler.
EDGY! Nicely bowled! Full on off, Woakes looks to drive but it takes the inside edge and onto the pads.
Well fielded! Full delivery on middle, Woakes drives it crisply towards the bowler. Afridi gets his foot in between. Saved a certain boundary there.
FOUR! That is beautifully timed! Good length ball outside off, Woakes drives it through the cover region for a boundary. The partnership moves to 40 off just 35 balls.
Good length ball on middle, Chris pushes it to mid on.
Excellent fielding in the deep! Saved a couple! Short ball around middle, Woakes pulls it to deep mid-wicket. The fielder comes across and tumbles to make the stop. Two runs taken.
Flatter outside off, Buttler pushes it to cover and takes a single.
Floated outside off, Woakes leaves it alone.
Loopy ball on middle, Woakes defends it back to the bowler.
Short ball outside off, Woakes punches it to deep cover for a single.

FOUR! Excellent batting from Jos Buttler! This partnership is keeping England in the game! Floated outside off, Buttler goes on his knees and reverse sweeps it to the deep point region for a boundary.
Tossed up on off, Buttler blocks it to cover.
Tossed up on middle, Woakes blocks it to point.
Loopy ball on middle, Woakes blocks it back to the bowler.
Flatter ball on off, Woakes punches it to cover.
On middle, Woakes flicks it to short leg.
Flighted on off, Woakes looks to defend but it takes the outside edge and goes towards third man. A single taken.

50-run stand comes up! Short ball on middle, Buttler pulls it to deep mid-wicket for a single. Excellent counterattacking cricket from England. They are in still with a chance, courtesy this partnership. TEA ON DAY 4.
Abbas starts with a good length ball on off, Buttler comes ahead and defends it to cover.
On a length on middle, Buttler pushes it to mid on.
BEATEN! Slashes but misses! Good length ball outside off, Buttler looks to slash but fails to make any connection to it.
First run of the session! Good length ball on middle, Jos works it to deep square leg for a single.
BEATEN! Nicely bowled! Good length ball outside off, Woakes looks to poke at it but misses it altogether.
Full on off, Woakes defends it out onto the pitch. Good start from Abbas.
Tossed up ball on middle, Buttler defends it towards mid on.
Low full toss outside off, Buttler drives it to long off for a single.
Well played! Floated outside off, Woakes creams the drive through cover for a single.
Shortish on off, Buttler moves in his crease and pushes it to long off for a single.
Loopy ball on off, Woakes drives it wide of mid off for a single.

FOUR! Excellent from Buttler! Brilliant over for England! 8 from it. Loopy ball outside off, Buttler drives it through extra cover. Yasir Shah runs across from long off but fails to stop it as the ball touches the fence.
Good length ball on middle, Woakes defends it back to the bowler.
On a length outside off, Woakes lets it go to the keeper.
Good length ball outside off, Chris pushes it to cover.
Full delivery on off, Woakes pushes it through the point region for a single. England need more 100.
On a length on off, Buttler blocks it to deep point for a single.
Slower ball outside off, Woakes taps it to deep point to collect another single.
BEATEN! That spun a long way! Floated ball outside off, spinning away. Woakes looks to defend but misses it altogether.
Shadab bowls a full toss on off, Woakes heaves it to the deep mid-wicket region and picks up a couple before the fielder cuts it off.
Full on the pads, Woakes flicks it to the leg side for a single.
Short ball on middle, Buttler pulls it to deep square leg for a single.
Fullish on middle, Chris pushes it to mid on.
Flighted outside off, Woakes drives it towards cover.
Good running! Length ball on off, Buttler pushes it to point and takes off for a single. The fielder has a shy at the bowler's end but misses. Buttler was well in though.
Good length ball on off, Woakes blocks it to cover off the back foot.
On a length on middle, Woakes flicks it to mid-wicket.
Full ball on middle, Woakes pushes it back to the bowler.
Good shot for nothing! Fullish ball outside off, Woakes prods forward and creams the drive but finds the cover fielder.
Short ball around middle, Woakes ducks under it.
BEATEN! Back of a length ball outside off, Buttler looks to cut but fails to get any bat on it.
Back of a length ball on off, Jos plays it to mid off.
Full this time on middle, JB blocks it onto the pitch.
Good length ball on off, Buttler solidly defends it to the cover region.
FOUR! Picks up the length perfectly! Excellent batting from Buttler! Short ball on off, Buttler pulls it to deep mid-wicket. The fielder runs across and dives but fails to stop it. A four signalled.
On a length outside off, Buttler leaves it alone.
PLAY AND A MISS! Poor shot! Not needed at this stage! Good length ball outside off, Woakes looks to drive but fails to make any connection.
Full on middle, Woakes flicks it to deep mid-wicket for a single.
On a length on the pads, Buttler tucks it to deep mid-wicket for a single.

FOUR! BEAUTIFUL FROM WOAKES! He has looked in incredible form since he came out to bat! Fullish ball on middle, Woakes flicks it wide of mid on for a boundary. More 83 needed for England. Azhar Ali does not look happy at all.
Good length ball on off, Woakes blocks it to cover.
Good length ball on middle, Woakes pushes it to mid on.
Good length ball on off, Buttler defends it to mid off.
Fullish ball on off, Buttler taps it to deep point for a single. Moves to 48.
SWING AND A MISS! Good length ball outside off, Woakes looks to heave it to the off side but the ball moves in and beats the edge of the bat. It goes on a bounce to the keeper.

FOUR! What a shot from Woakes! He is playing a gem of an innings here! Good length ball outside off, Woakes guides it to the third man region for a boundary. The fielder tries hard to stop it with a dive but fails to do so.

Almost worked! Short ball almost does the trick for Pakistan! Short ball around off, Woakes looks to pull but it takes the top edge. Yasir tries his level best to catch it but the ball lands safely. A single taken. 200 up for England. They need more 77 runs.
Short ball around off, Buttler sways away from it.
Just short! Fullish ball on off, Woakes drives it uppishly. Luckily, it lands safely in front of the mid off fielder.
Good length ball on middle, Chris works it to mid-wicket.
On a length on off, Woakes guides it to gully.
Shortish on middle, Woakes pulls it to deep square leg for a single.
Good length delivery on middle, Buttler defends it to mid on.
Moves to 49! Full delivery on the middle and leg stump line, Buttler whips it to deep mid-wicket for a single.

FIFTY! 17th Test fifty for Jos Buttler! An important one for his side and himself! He had a tough time with the gloves but is making amends in this knock. His job is not done yet and he needs to take his side home. Short ball on middle, Buttler pulls it to fine leg for a single.

FOUR! Well played! Woakes got into a tangle playing the short ball in Naseem's last over but not this time! Short ball outside off, Woakes makes room and plays it over the cover region for a boundary.

FOUR! 5th Test fifty for Chris Woakes! This has been a top class innings from Woakes! He and Buttler are taking England closer and closer to victory! Brilliant stuff. Fullish ball outside off, Woakes lunges forward and drives it through the cover region for another boundary.
On a length outside off, Woakes leaves it alone.
Good length ball on middle, Woakes looks to flick but it takes the inside edge and it goes to deep square leg. A single taken.
Full ball on middle, Buttler pushes it wide of mid on and picks up a single. 11 from the over. An excellent one for England.
An appeal for LBW turned down! Loopy ball on the pads, Buttler looks to sweep but gets hit on the pads. There is a mild appeal for LBW but the umpire is not interested.
Tossed up on the pads, Buttler sweeps it to deep square leg for a single.
Tossed up on off, Woakes lunges forward and defends it to cover.
Flatter one on off, Chris blocks it to point.
On off, pushed to cover off the front foot.
Floated on middle, Woakes defends it back to the bowler.
Full ball on off, Buttler drives it to mid off.
Good length ball on middle, Buttler works it wide of mid on for a run.
Very full on middle, Woakes digs it out to mid on.
Full on middle, Woakes defends it to the off side.
Fuller on middle, Woakes flicks it to mid on for a single.
Good length ball on middle, Buttler defends it back to the bowler.
Tossed up delivery on off, Woakes drives it to covers.
Short delivery on off, Woakes makes room and cuts it through point for a single. 100-run stand is up between Woakes and Buttler.
Flighted delivery on middle, Buttler looks to sweep but gets hit on the shoulder.
Loopy delivery on off, Buttler pushes it towards covers for a run.
Floated delivery outside off, Woakes shoulders arms to this one.
On off, Woakes works it to mid on for a single.
Short ball outside off, Woakes guides it to the third man region for a single.
On a length on off, Buttler shuffles across and looks to flick but gets a leading edge which goes to cover.
Back of a length ball on off, Buttler defends it back to the bowler.
Full delivery on the pads, Buttler looks to flick but it takes the inside edge, hits the pads and rolls to fine leg for a couple.
Good length ball on off, Buttler blocks it to cover.
Outside off, not played at.
Tossed up delivery on off, Woakes defends it off the front foot.
Flighted delivery on middle, Woakes drives it to mid on.
Loopy delivery on off, Woakes looks to defend but gets an outside edge. It goes towards third man. The batsmen get two runs.
On middle, Woakes blocks it well.
Full delivery on middle, Woakes drives it to mid on.
Loopy delivery on off, Woakes drives it through mid off for a run.
Full delivery on off, Woakes pushes it to cover.
Short ball outside off, Woakes punches it to deep cover and picks up a couple. England need only 50.
Very full delivery on off, Woakes digs it out to point.
A single now! Fullish ball outside off, Woakes drives it to cover. Yasir dives and makes a half stop, allowing the batters to take a single.
Very full delivery on middle, almost a yorker. Buttler plays it back to the bowler.
On a length on off, Buttler blocks it to cover.
Loopy ball down the leg side, Woakes looks to flick but misses.
Just short! Lovely leg spinner from Yasir Shah! Floated on off, Woakes looks to defend but it takes the gloves and goes towards the slip cordon. Luckily, it lands safely.
Play and a miss! Short ball outside off, Woakes looks to cut off the back foot but fails to get any bat on it.
Tossed up on middle, Woakes works it to square leg for a single.
Flighted on middle, Jos tucks it to deep square leg for a single.
On middle, Chris defends it out.
Full delivery outside off, Buttler pushes it to cover.
NO BALL! Good length ball outside off, Buttler leaves it alone. The third umpire conveys it to the on-field umpire that it is a No Ball.
Length ball outside off, Buttler leaves it alone.
Good length ball on off, Buttler blocks it to the cover region.
Fullish on middle, Jos pushes it to mid off.
On a length on middle, Jos defends it out to the point region.
Slower ball on middle, Buttler flicks it to deep square leg and collects a couple. Good running from the two batters. 44 more runs to win.
Floated outside off, Woakes leaves it alone.
Full delivery outside off, Woakes drives it to deep cover for a single.

NOT OUT! The Ultra Edge shows no spike! Excellent decision from the on-field umpire though. Floated ball outside off, Buttler looks to cut but he seems to have missed. Pakistan think that Buttler has edged and they take the review. The Ultra Edge rolls in and it shows no spike as the ball passes the bat. Pakistan had to take the review in desperation and they lose one.
What happened there? Lots of turn there! Floated ball on off, Buttler looks to defend but the ball spins in and hits Buttler on the shoulder.
BEATEN! Loopy ball outside off, Buttler looks to defend but fails to get any bat on it.
Flighted on middle, Buttler reverse sweeps it to third man for a single.
Full delivery on off, Buttler drives it through mid off for a run.
Flighted delivery on middle, Woakes blocks it off the front foot.
On middle, Woakes comes down the track and defends it.

NOT OUT! Missing the off stump! Wasted review! Probably took in desperation! Flighted ball on off, Woakes goes on his knees to paddle sweep but misses and gets hit on the pads. There is an appeal for LBW but the umpire is not interested. Azhar Ali takes ages to decide whether to take the review. The Ball Tracker rolls in and it shows that it is missing the off stump. Pakistan lose all their reviews.
Full on middle, Woakes pushes it to mid on.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
Tossed up delivery outside off, Buttler leaves it alone.
Floated delivery just outside off, Buttler shoulders arms to this one.
Loopy delivery on off, Buttler guides it towards third man. The batsmen cross ends.
Flighted delivery on off, Woakes punches it through covers. The batsmen pick up a couple.
Full delivery on off, Woakes drives it through covers for a single.
On middle, Buttler flicks it through mid-wicket for a run.

Lands safely! Very lucky for Jos Buttler. Pakistan desperately needed that go into the hands of the fielder! Short ball on middle, Buttler looks to pull but it takes the top edge. It goes towards deep mid-wicket but lands safely. A single.
Tossed up on middle, Woakes defends it back to the bowler.
Outside off, Woakes drives it to deep cover for a single.
Flighted on middle, Buttler looks to flick but gets a leading edge back to the bowler.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Floated outside off, Buttler pushes it to cover.
Tossed up delivery outside off, Woakes offers no shot to this one.
Flighted delivery just outside off, Woakes lets it go.
Full delivery on off, Woakes drives it through covers for a run.
Loopy delivery on middle, Jos keeps it out.
Floated delivery on off, Buttler plays a reverse sweep towards covers.
Outside off, Jos does not bother to play at that.
Floated on middle, Woakes looks to work it to the leg side but gets a leading edge back to the bowler.
Tosses this one on off, Woakes pushes it to mid off.
Excellent fielding! Shan Masood has done really well! Flighted ball outside off, Woakes drives it wide of mid off. Masood dives and makes a terrific stop. Saved a certain boundary.
Short ball outside off, Woakes punches it to deep cover for a single.
SIX! A rank long-hop and Buttler makes full use of it. England need more 26 runs. Short ball on middle, Buttler pulls it over the deep mid-wicket region for a maximum.
Loopy ball on middle, Buttler flicks it to mid-wicket and keeps the strike for the next over.
Flighted on middle, Buttler whips it to deep square leg and collects a couple.
Flatter one outside off, Buttler leaves it alone.
Loopy ball on middle, Buttler reverse sweeps it to the deep point region for another couple.
The batsman shows the full face of the bat and defends the ball off the back foot.

OUT! LBW! Is there twist in the tale? Buttler has to go but after playing a terrific innings. He has almost taken his side home! Yasir has his third wicket. Loopy ball on middle, Buttler looks to play the reverse but misses and gets hit on the pads. Pakistan appeal and the umpire raises the finger. Buttler takes the review. The Ultra Edge shows no bat and the Ball Tracker shows that it is umpire's call on impact and hitting the stumps. End of a very good innings from Jos Buttler.
Floated on middle, Broad sweeps it to the deep square leg region for a single.
Tossed up delivery on off, Broad keeps it out.
FOUR! Nicely played! Loopy delivery on middle, Broad sweeps it through square leg for a boundary.
On middle, Broad defends it off the back foot.
Floated delivery on middle, Broad sweeps it through square leg for a single.
Flighted delivery on off, Woakes blocks it off the back foot.
On off, Woakes defends it to covers.
Floated on middle, Broad sweeps it but it hits the short leg fielder.
Flatter one on middle, Woakes flicks it to short leg.
Full on middle, Broad sweeps but straight to deep square leg. Only a single.
BEATEN! Lovely from Yasir! He has bowled his heart out! Flighted outside off, Woakes looks to defend but fails to get any bat on it.
BEATEN! Another beautiful delivery! Tossed up ball outside off, Woakes attempts to defend but fails to get any bat on it.
Full toss on middle, Woakes flicks it to deep square leg for a single.
Some swing straightaway with the second new ball! The line though is down the leg side. Woakes looks to flick but misses.
No swing on this delivery! It is on a length and around off, Woakes keeps it out easily.
Inside edge! Needless stroke there! It is full and outside off, the sucker ball. Woakes goes after it wide from the body. He gets an inside edge onto the pads.
NO BALL! Outside off, it is left alone. The third umpire conveys the message that Shaheen has overstepped. 12 more needed.
10 more needed now! A couple. Catch it was the call but it is away from the fielder. Full and outside off, it is driven wide of the fielder at deep point and two is taken.
FOUR! Lovely! Probably the shot which seals the deal for England. 6 more needed. Fuller and on middle, this is creamed through mid off and it races away to the fence.
Just the 5 needed now! A short ball on middle, Woakes pulls it through square leg and a run is taken.
Short ball outside off, Woakes cuts it to deep point for a single. England are just a wicket away.

OUT! LBW! Is it too late for Pakistan? Yasir has picked up the wicket with the new ball! Fourth wicket for him. Floated on middle, Broad looks to sweep but misses and gets hit on the pads. Pakistan appeal and the umpire raises his finger. Broad does not review and simply walks back. Root watches from the dressing room nervously. The Ball Tracker rolls in and it shows that it was plumb in front.
Flatter on middle, Bess defends it out.

Quicker one on middle and leg, Bess looks to flick but misses and gets rapped on the pads. There is an appeal for LBW but nothing from the umpire. The replays show that he had hit it with the bat first.
Flatter one on off, Bess is in two minds whether to defend it or leave. The ball takes the edge and rolls to the slip cordon.
Full outside off, Bess pushes it to cover.

EDGY FOUR! That's the end of this game! What a wonderful chase from England! They were down and out in this game but Woakes and Buttler have done it. They have won it for England. Good length ball on middle, Woakes looks to flick but it takes the leading edge and goes through the slip cordon and into the third man fence. ENGLAND WIN BY THREE WICKETS.
